e18 exit at drengsrud; truck and possibly a passenger car with a stop. information to us indicates that the lorry is on the shoulder, but it creates queues anyway. salvage is underway.

a police patrol stopped a car for inspection. the car had several passengers, and after some investigation the patrol suspected that the driver was transporting people for a fee, without holding a valid taxi license ("pirate taxi"). the driver is reported for the relationship.
car with a stop in lrentunnelen, ring , westbound. standing in the right field.

we are done on the spot. the woman is taken to the emergency department for a check-up, but appears unharmed. we have spoken to witnesses, the tram driver and the woman. in total, it appears that there was an accident where the woman entered the side of the tram and fell.
the scene has been cleared and the tram is running as normal again through storgata.
the woman who was hit appears to be in good health, she is being checked by the ambulance now. we are in conversation with the tram driver and witnesses to form a picture of the sequence of events.
the tram is at the site, there is a stoppage in the lines that go through storgata out of the city centre.
a person at storgata is said to have been hit by the tram. the person is described as awake and alert. the emergency services are on their way.
the missing girl has been found safe and sound.
the car has been removed. the driver was taken to the emergency room for a check-up. we are opening a case and have confiscated the driver's license.
there are slightly different explanations of the course of events between the parties, but we have expelled three people from the area. a case is established based on coercion/threats.
traffic accident on e6 inbound eastbound, before ryenkrysset. for now, only reports of single accidents. stands in the right lane before the ryen exit. traffic runs smoothly in other areas.

we are in greenland after a person was allegedly threatened with a knife. we have been able to control three people in connection with the incident. no one was injured and we are now investigating what happened.
the site is then cleared and traffic flows as normal at the site. we create a case.

the emergency services are in engervannsveien because a car has hit a fence. one person sent to hospital, extent of damage unclear. there is also said to have been a diesel leak which the fire service is working on.

the police have been notified of a man who has been down the tracks at jernbanetorget subway station. the subway was stopped for a period while guards took the person onto the platform. we have a conversation with the man together with amb. the subway is now in normal operation.

the police have carried out a crime scene investigation and will investigate the accident. the injured person has been taken to okl for further health supervision, but the message from health is that he is not seriously injured. the accident has had no consequences for train traffic. the emergency services are ready at the scene.

the emergency services have just arrived on the scene. the accident is an occupational accident, where a worker has fallen in the area of bane nor in lodalen. we have contact with the injured person who is awake, not seriously injured. we treat this as an occupational accident.

the emergency services are on their way to lodalen, where we have received a report of an accident. we are investigating whether this is an occupational accident and what the extent and possible consequences are for train traffic.
the emergency services are ready at the scene. the police will investigate the fire.
we have held a traffic control in kvrner town with a focus on securing children in cars. as part of this control, we have given advice and guidance to motorists regarding this.

several residents were evacuated due to the development of smoke, but these are now back in their apartments. work is now underway at the site to gain an overview of the extent of the damage, both from the fire, smoke and water damage.
no injuries were reported in connection with the fire.

the emergency services are at gullhella in asker following a report of a fire in a vehicle. the vehicle is in a garage basement next to an apartment building. the fire brigade has control of the fire.

the driver is sent for treatment with minor injuries. the police opened a case and the driver's license was confiscated due to suspicion of negligent driving. the emergency services are ready at the scene.

only the driver in the car. does not appear to be seriously injured, but is being examined by an ambulance. the lamp post is checked for damage. the car has been recovered. traffic can drive past the site.
ring westbound exit ramp to nils hansen's road. single accident car. driven into a lamppost. the emergency services are on their way.
we are receiving several reports of banging/shooting in the adamstuen area, the armed forces are practicing and the police are aware of this. it will last until friday.

it has burned in a "pool" of rubbish measuring approximately x20 metres. a few bangs were heard ahead of the fire. it is possible that some batteries have exploded. the fire brigade stays behind and puts out the fire. case is created.
the fire service reports that they have control and are working to extinguish the last remnants of the fire. it appears that no one is injured, but some workers are checked by the ambulance on site.
there will be a fire in a hydraulic system inside the site, there is a risk of spreading. the fire extinguishing system installed on site has subdued the fire somewhat.
the emergency services are on their way to haraldrud recycling station after reports of a fire. it is unclear and there is a possible risk of spread. there must be smoke in the area.
the sick list has been checked out and appears unharmed. this is resolved with a claim report between the parties. we are done on the spot.
ambulance and we are at bygdylokket after a car and bicycle have collided. the sick list is being checked by an ambulance now. traffic flows past the site.
police and the fire service responded to an oil leak at tsen center today. a lorry had leaked hydraulic oil in kaj munk's path. it has been cleaned up after the leak and we are opening a case.
the fire is now out.

the fire brigade has control on the scene. driver post-shutdown. the resident is taken by ambulance for a check-up. inhaled some smoke. cause of fire unknown, but possible fire in a charger for an electric motorcycle.
the emergency services are on the scene. the fire more or less extinguished by the resident. some smoke still. no risk of spreading.
the emergency services are on their way to an address on mortensrud after reports of a fire in a garage.
the person has been found and is safe.

we are looking for a missing girl. possible last sighting is in the tollbugata area. description: girl, south american appearance. about cm tall, long black hair, possible in a ponytail. black glasses, possibly wearing a dark blue winter jacket. brown eyes, moles on face
we have stopped a motorist on ring near ullevl after several reports of erratic driving. suspect inflated to far above legal value. driver's license bracket.
motorist stopped in nedre kalbakkenvei, driving without a valid driver's license. we are filing a case on the relationship.
we have stopped a motorist suspected of driving under the influence of drugs. we create a report.

the emergency services are in sofienberggata, where there has been a fire in a garbage truck. the fire probably started in the garbage compartment of the car. the fire brigade is now in control. no personal injury reported.
the car has been removed.
tow truck is required. slow moving queue past the place.
e6 inbound towards oslo v/ furuset. car that has a puncture. stands in the middle field. we are on our way.
we have picked up the person in question and are transporting him away from the road.
several reports of a man walking along the roadside on the e18 inbound towards oslo. we are on our way.
the road is opened.
we are directing traffic through asker town center in anticipation of car recovery. long queues on site.
e18 direction oslo. traffic accident just before the center of asker. a car has driven into the guard rail and is blocking the entire road. the emergency services and tow truck are en route.
storgata. fight between several people. no one appears to be seriously injured. we have control on site.
we have control on site. there are no injuries.

we have an unresolved situation at ensj. threats have been made against the emergency services in connection with an assignment. we are working on site, and there will be a number of emergency vehicles and reduced accessibility on site for a period.

trafikk and rytterkorpset have had contact and safety-creating patrols in oslo today. there, among others, the traffic corps was out with its old volvo patrol car from . the patrols got in good contact with the city's citizens on their rounds in oslo.
talk about a chicken that has been forgotten in the oven, this has resulted in heavy smoke. the fire brigade vents out. those involved have been checked out for health on the spot.

appears as heavy smoke from the kitchen in an apartment. work is underway to confirm from what and whether there is a risk of spread. two people have been taken out of an apartment, these are checked by health for smoke exposure.

the emergency services are on their way to bjrndal after reports of a fire in a block of flats. there must be several people who have evacuated themselves and there is visible smoke coming from the place.
no one has been arrested so far, but we have some information to work from. several investigations have been carried out, traces secured and interrogations taken in the case.
blood samples will be taken from those involved, suspected of driving under the influence of drugs. case is created.
the victim is conscious, and has injuries that may be compatible with stab wounds. the victim will be taken to hospital. we are searching for the perpetrator, and have some information to work from.
police and ambulance are on the way after a report that a person is likely to have been stabbed.
towing is required. both people are taken to the emergency department for a check-up.
major material damage to the car. two people involved appear to be unharmed. traffic in the northbound direction runs in one lane.
report of traffic accident on rv4 northbound at linderud. probably only one vehicle involved. the police are on their way.
the fire has been extinguished, and one lane has been opened up.

the fire brigade has arrived and extinguished the fire. as of now, no risk of spread has been reported, and probably no injuries. the e6 inbound direction will be closed until we have the fire under control.
e6 inbound after klemetsrud: heavy fire in vehicle. the emergency services are on their way.
the fire probably started when the person lit the fireplace and, as a result, the person's clothes caught fire. the person has been taken to hospital with serious burns.
the fire is extinguished. only one person was found in the apartment who was seriously burned. we are now investigating the cause of the fire. the fire is confined to an apartment.

we and an ambulance on the way to askeveien after a report of a fire in an apartment. the fire brigade is just on the scene. a person must be seriously injured. the fire brigade has started extinguishing.
we are on the scene and the grass fire is now almost out. a resident has inhaled some smoke and an ambulance is on the way to check on the person concerned.
we and the fire brigade are on their way to munkebekken after reports of a grass fire. some try to put it out on the spot, but fail to do so. the fire is close to a block of flats at the site.
we are done on the spot. the driver of the car is suspected of breaching the duty to yield and a case has been opened. the driver had his driver's license confiscated on the spot.
we are on the scene. has control on both parties. kick cyclist is slightly injured. we are investigating what the course of events may be.
we and an ambulance are on our way to a traffic accident between a motorist and a kick cyclist in the roundabout by the national theatre. the extent of the damage is currently unknown.
one car was towed away, and the other two are drivable. no personal injuries. the road has been reopened.
a person had his car keys stolen. suspect ran from the scene. a patrol has now taken control of the suspect.

we are in contact with a victim who is said to have been subjected to violence. the person has suffered injuries to the face. we have no control over the suspects, and are investigating the background to the incident.
three cars involved. no personal injury reported. need for towing away.
we are in greenland following a report of a person who is said to have been kicked by several others. we are investigating what happened.

at the e6 entrance at karihaugen there has been a traffic accident between three cars. the traffic flows smoothly past. the case is resolved by reporting the damage, and a vehicle must be towed from the scene.
e18 entrance at blommenholm. in connection with a vehicle stop, there has been a chain collision at the rear of the stop. patrol is on the scene.
no knife found on any of those checked.
several people ran when the police arrived. we have control over two of these, and are investigating whether they have any role in this.
we are in greenland after a report of a person who is said to have been threatened with a knife by another person in vaterlandsparken.

a vy train was exposed to damage in the form of graffiti. the suspect had an unpleasant encounter with the diligent dog patrol. dog and dog handler took off. suspects were caught up like a boomerang. luckily he wasn't bitten. review or not, is not contested.

a car driver had to hand in his driving license after a speeding offence. the person was measured at km/h in the zone. the police will continue their control activities and presence in traffic, also at night, with the aim of preventing serious traffic accidents.

we have arrested a young boy we associate with the firework shooting. the person concerned has been expelled from oslo city centre. we take the incident seriously, there is obviously a risk of personal injury and material damage.

we are at jernbanetorget with several patrols after what is described as youths have shot fireworks along the hill towards, among other things, a restaurant where several people had to jump away to avoid being hit.

we have received several reports that license plates on parked cars at ryken train station have been changed, we ask those who have parked there in the last couple of weeks to check that they have the correct license plate on their car both front and back.
the emergency services are ready at the scene. we create an investigation case.
the fire service reports that they are now under control and that it was probably only a warm-up with smoke development.
the emergency services are at storsand wharf after a report of smoke from a boat, probably from the battery. no one is injured and there is no risk of spreading.

one of our patrols has stopped a car that exhibited bad driving behavior by being too close to the driver in front. the driver is also suspected of driving under the influence of drugs. further investigations are carried out, and the driver's license is temporarily confiscated.
we have held a blood alcohol test on rykenveien near eidsletta. checked, no reaction from the police.
we have held a blood alcohol test in brynsveien in sandvika. did not check any reactions from the police.
stopped a motorist after a report of erratic driving and varying speed on the e18 inbound from asker. the driver appeared to be under the influence of drugs and we are opening a case.

a patrol from the traffic corps observed the traffic on the e6 last night.a total of reactions to speeding, of which drivers lost their driving license because they drove over km/h in the zone. top speed was km/h.
fire brigade and police on site. there is only talk of a smoldering fire in a rubbish bin. no risk of spreading.
the emergency services are on their way to an address on rodelkka after reports of a fire in a backyard.
we have interviewed both parties. failure to give way is the cause of the accident. one of the people involved was taken to the emergency department for a check-up. we open a case.

traffic accident in the smedstad junction with two motorists involved. the parties involved must have moved to a more suitable location. no reports of serious personal injury as of now. we are on our way.
we are there and the fire service has extinguished the fire. about square meters that have burned. no damage to buildings or anything else. we are investigating the cause of the grass fire.
we and the fire service are on their way to a report of a grass fire in martin skatvedt's road.
the dog was taken to a vet and attempts were made to revive it, but unfortunately it died as a result of drowning.

the fire service found the dog under water. it is unconscious. life-saving first aid is now being given to the dog. the person who was responsible for the dog is on site and is being looked after by us.
we and the fire service are at the opera and are looking for a dog that has fallen into the water. the fire service has divers in the water now.
one of our patrols stopped a car driver who was driving at km/h in a signposted zone. the driver is reported and has his driver's license temporarily confiscated.
the car has been parked on the spot. the kick cyclist has lost some teeth. stays with the ambulance for follow-up. not seriously injured.the police are opening a case.

we are at rosenhoff regarding a traffic accident between a kick cyclist and a car. preliminary information at the scene may indicate that the kick cyclist has driven into the car. no information on serious injuries, but the driver of the scooter is bruised.

the man was unable to take care of himself, but tried as hard as the police spoke to him to run into a new door. fortunately, he did not succeed in this.he has been taken into custody and is being reported for disorderly conduct.

security guards at a building in bjrvika saw on camera a man who apparently tried to break in through a glass door. this shortly after a passer-by had been bothered by the same man.we got control of a very drunk man just around the corner.

one of our hypotheses, based on the video and witnesses, is that the victims were offered drugs, whereupon they became irritated because of this, and were therefore exposed to violence in the disagreement that arose.

further investigations show that the two victims do not live at the hotel in question. we have not found these two men.we have secured traces and ids of the two arrested, and they will be dismissed from the scene.we encourage the victims to contact the police.

we now have control over several people at the bottom of trondheimsveien who we are investigating to see if they are behind the violence.we have not come into contact with the two tourists, but are working in parallel with that as well.

an employee at a hotel reported that two polish tourists had been subjected to violence in vaterlandsparken and that they were probably on their way to the emergency room with cuts to the head.we received a description of suspects who we have searched for in the area.

the vehicles involved in the traffic accident have been recovered.e18 will soon be opened, what remains is a small damage report in relation to a traffic accident that occurred at the rear of the first accident.
drone image from the scene.30-50 meters of wire railings are damaged. salvage is on site.we have questioned the driver and are investigating further to find out how the accident happened.

the car was pulling a trailer that was transporting another car. this has ended up in the center divider and caused quite a lot of damage there, as well as soil ending up in the roadway. we are working to secure video of the incident from other motorists. two fields are still blocked.

we are on site and we are waiting for recovery. the overturned trailer has lost some soil which must be removed from the left field. two fields are blocked so far.the accident happened approximately km after the collision from asker towards holmen.

there has been a traffic accident on the e18 inbound between asker and holmen. we have been informed that there is a single accident. no injuries have been reported. the traffic flows smoothly, but it leads to queues. the emergency services are on the scene.
patrulje stopped a drunk driver at bondi. he blew over the legal limit, and a blood test is secured. we have confiscated the driver's license of the suspect.
the emergency services have finished on site, and the subway will run as normal.
the emergency services are at blindern subway station, with a report that a person has been hit by a subway. subway traffic is stopped at the site.

three young people of secondary school age are reported for disorderly conduct. guardians and child protection have been informed and they have been expelled from the area.the situation has been calm after the fight, and we have been and will continue to be present throughout the evening.
the suspect was so drunk that he was taken into police custody. no one was injured and luckily the situation was somewhat milder than was initially described.

an intoxicated person was rude to the conductor on the train. another passenger reacted to this and helped the conductor to get the rude man off the train. no one was injured and the train can now move on.

we are at alna station following a report from a conductor about a fight on a train. it was not reported that the two involved we now have control of are injured, but it was described as both being on the floor and fighting. the local train is standing still at the platform until further notice.
most of the young people ran in all directions, and we remained on the scene with several patrols to prevent during the evening, as well as to unravel the fight.

we are inside and outside oslo s with several patrols and have been for the last hour. the background is reports of bad mood between young people.a short time ago it was more than amps and we had to break up into a bigger fight. no injuries reported.
the cars have been removed and the road has been cleared. a driver has his license confiscated when he ran a red light and caused the accident.

the people involved are in a stable condition and are being checked by paramedics at the scene. a person probably has a broken bone in an arm. work is underway to remove the cars to improve traffic flow.
traffic accident between two cars at the intersection of monolittveien and ullernchaussee. will cause traffic challenges in the area.
the extent of the damage still appears to be unclear, but there may be critical damage. relatives of the child are cared for in the hospital. the driver is taken care of by the police.
must be a child who has been hit. the extent of the damage is unclear. the child is taken to hospital by ambulance. the driver is checked on the spot.
the emergency services are on their way to tjuvholmen following reports of a traffic accident between a person and a vehicle. undetermined course of events and extent of damage.
the car was towed away and normal traffic at the scene.
we're here. a small fire in a car has now been extinguished. no personal injury. we are waiting for car towing. two out of three lanes are blocked. a bit of a queue at the site.
e6 inbound at karihaugen. all emergency services on their way after a report of a fire in a car. left field is blocked.
the e6 is now open to normal traffic again.
the e6 exit at helsfyr is closed to traffic in a field.

all emergency services are on e6 exiting at helsfyr. a young boy has been hit by a car. it may seem as if the boy has run/walked straight into the road. the boy is injured, but not critically. we are investigating what has happened and trying to find relatives of the boy.

we have not yet made contact with the driver. however, we have no reason to believe that the driver is seriously injured. the car is in the process of being recovered and the road cleared of fallout.the police are opening a case and will investigate the matter further.

the emergency services are in romss following a report of a traffic accident. a car involved, which ended up lying on its side. driver was observed leaving the scene.major material damage to the vehicle.

the police received a report earlier last night about three cars driving recklessly and dangerously on the e6 towards the center of oslo. the relevant drivers were caught a little later. all three are reported and have had their driving licenses confiscated.
we and the fire brigade are there. turned out to be only a fire alarm and we leave the place.
fire alarm from an apartment in johan scharffenbergs vei. in addition, it smells of smoke. so far no reports of injuries or evacuees.
case is created.
capralhaugen. there was a fire in an apartment. a person in the apartment is being examined by an ambulance. probably did not inhale any smoke. the fire is extinguished.
the fire brigade has control of the fire. a person is exposed to smoke. most residents can return to their respective apartments.
we are in granstangen where something may be burning in a kitchen. black smoke and the smell of burnt plastic. -30 people have evacuated themselves.

we have no concrete description of the perpetrators, but we are interested in getting in touch with -8 young people dressed in black who have both been observed at storo by circle k and sinsen subway station approx. at .

we have come across a person with stab wounds at torshov. the victim must have been the victim of a robbery at sinsen subway station before he was found. the victim is to be considered slightly injured. any witnesses to the robbery are asked to call the police on .
we are done on the spot. not sure what actually happened. the person who was down was uninjured.
a person knocked down at the plaza. we are searching for two people who ran from the scene. the victim may have been unconscious, but we are talking to him now.

we have control over two young people who threatened and robbed a jacket on skyen. the jacket was found near the place where the young people were encountered. talk about verbal threats. we are now questioning those involved.

we have been in osterhaus street where there has been a collision between a cyclist and a car. the cyclist with pain in his arm and foot and is checked at the emergency room. no driver's license seizure, but the police open a case.
the car has been removed and the road is open to traffic again.
we are on site in connection with a traffic stop on the e18 outbound between holmen and asker. bilberger is requisitioned. lots of traffic and long queues at the site.
the man who was in the house when the firemen were taken care of is safe. he is not physically injured. we are filing a case on the relationship.
we are filing a case on the relationship. the main hypothesis is that the fire started in a fan oven, but it is unclear why. the emergency services have left the scene.
we have opened a case and the entire equipment has been towed in.

the fire brigade has been up in the attic and put out some flames there. unclear what it has burned in for now. the person(s) who were in the house initially have evacuated themselves. no injuries reported.
the emergency services are in briskeveien following a report of smoke in an attic in a detached house. the fire service is working to clarify the extent.

the emergency services are in tokes vei where there has been a fire in a kitchen. the fire has been extinguished, but the fire service is working to clarify the extent of the fire. no injuries reported, but we do not have a complete overview yet.
we have opened a case for a breach of section of the road traffic act, where the lorry driver who backed up on the e18 is suspected.
upon further investigation, it turned out that both the van and the trailer had been deregistered. briefly explained, it means that the driver should not have been on the road today.

reporter observed a crew with van and trailer where the load appeared poorly secured. in addition, the registration number on the trailer was written in marker.we have stopped the driver at lambertseter and are now investigating what consequences this transport will have.
the traffic accident has not caused significant traffic problems.

a lorry driver found out in time, but still too late, that the lorry was too high to pass under the bygdylokket. he therefore backed up to take off before the lid. he backed into a van that was coming up behind at low speed. we are in contact with the parties.

the car that the suspect twice drove while intoxicated has been temporarily banned from use. the signs have been taken and the car has been towed in.suspect reported for two counts of drunk driving and one count of driving without a valid driver's license.

last night at around a man was caught for drink-driving on tjuvholmen. a blood test was taken, the driver's license was revoked and he was dismissed.at the same man was caught driving again, this time at hosle in brum.we are investigating whether the man has stolen mobile phones from a hotel as well.
we have finished the crime scene investigation, a case is being opened. the arrested person has been taken into custody, reported for burglary and several violations of the road traffic act.

we are nils hansen's path after a burglary. in this connection, we came across a car that tried to elude control. this car was pursued by us and stopped on skyen, where we have arrested a person and we are looking for several people who ran from the car.
the fire is extinguished, the car is towed in for possible further investigations. case is created.
the emergency services are in evjetun at no. after a report of a fire in a vehicle. there are open flames from a car and the fire brigade is putting it out.

we are done on the spot, we have carried out both tactical and technical investigative steps. we have searched for the perpetrator without success in the local area. we have traces and a description which we are following up and our patrols continue with the person in question throughout the night.

we are searching for a perpetrator in the area. it is said to have been threatened with a gun-like object and an amount of cash was stolen from the scene. we also carry out investigative steps on site.
we are at ensj bingo. there has been a robbery of the bingo, there must have been a threat with a weapon. we are searching for the perpetrator in the area.
e18 outbound v/ vker. car with stop. we are on site, tow truck requested.
the bus has been saved. the road is open to normal traffic.
tow truck is on site.
.eufemiasgate bus out of service. standing eastbound direction at x nyladsveien. creates some traffic challenges, but the traffic passes. tow truck is required.

collision from behind. the cars have been removed and the road is open. the driver of one car is suspected of driving under the influence of drugs. prepared for blood sampling. reported and driver's license confiscated.
police and ambulance on site. collision from behind. no personal injury. need for vehicle salvage.
the emergency services are on their way to e6 ingde, ulvensplitten. collision between two vehicles. unknown extent of damage.
the police are finished at the scene. the victim is described as stable. the two arrested have been charged with attempted murder. we hope to question them during the day.
the crime scene is at a private address, we are still working on the scene with investigative steps.
we have arrested two people we associate with the incident. both are taken into custody.
the person is prepared.

we are at torshov after a person is said to have been stabbed with a sharp object. the person is described as critically injured and taken to hospital. we work on site with technical and tactical investigations.

we are looking for a -year-old woman who is missing from dnski. has asberger's, cognitive impairment and poor balance. probably walks with a walker and is cm tall. has a normal build, but with a slightly large stomach. short hair and is dressed in a black jacket and blue jeans.
there is control on site, talk about a wire that has come into contact with a furnace. no one was injured and all the evacuees have gone back inside.
the emergency services are in karlsborgveien following a report of smoke in a room. several residents have evacuated themselves.
offender taken care of by health. no one was arrested in the case, and the matter is being reported.

we have control over everyone involved. we contact parents/guardians of all. two people are reported for violence against the police.

the police were at the scene on another mission when the atmosphere became tense. two officials have been beaten in connection with this. we are still on the scene with more patrols, as the tense atmosphere persists. those involved are young adults.
we are at oslo s with a number of patrols as there is a tense atmosphere with several young people on site.
the person who was taken into custody is considered to have been arrested. no further involvement found. we have ended the operational effort.
the missing, demented man is now safe and sound.

we have control over a likely perpetrator. the person is taken into custody. still working on talking to witnesses. no find of any axe. have not come into contact with, or been notified of, anyone injured.

we have been, and are, searching with several patrols in the area. we are now checking some people who may have been involved in this. so far no discovery of the said axe. no reports of anyone being injured either.

the police are in the storgata area following a report of a fight between several people, one of whom is said to have had an axe. as of now, there are no reports of any injuries. we have no control over suspects.

the man is still missing, and we want feedback from the public regarding information that may be of importance to the case. refers to previously published image on twitter. call us on tel. for observation.
police patrol on site. the vehicles in question have left the roadway. no traffic problems. no injuries reported.

the emergency services are on their way to enebakkveien close to ryenkrysset where a traffic accident has been reported. several cars are said to be involved, but no one is said to be seriously injured. may cause traffic challenges.
the missing persons visited an elderly center in oscars gate about minutes ago. we are continuing the search for him in surrounding areas.
the missing are safe and sound.
