bilberger is on site and takes a car with him. the other car involved is said to have driven away from the scene and not stopped after the accident.
kongsveien is completely blocked. major material damage to the cars involved. no report of serious injuries.
not much traffic in the area at the time of the accident. bilberger is on site.
this is in the ekeberg area, not the ekeberg tunnel as first reported.
traffic accident on brumveien near gjettum. likely hit from behind. car recovery is on its way. no report of personal injury.
traffic accident, head to head, kongsveien. the emergency services are on their way. notification of material damage. it is not clear whether there is personal injury.
then the last car has been recovered and the road is open to normal traffic. we are filing a case on the relationship. appears as a chain collision with three images involved.
we are on site, talk about material damage to the cars, a car needs to be salvaged. traffic is diverted past in a field.
report of traffic accident in breivollveien. should be three cars involved. no report of personal injury. we are on our way.
we managed to get the semi-trailer on the right keel and thus all fields are open on e6 inbound again.
the semi-trailer has been moved so that one lane is now open. a tow truck is on its way to solve the problem further.
a semi-trailer has ended up partially across the road on the e6 inbound at teisen. all three fields are blocked until further notice. no injuries and we are working on site to remove the trailer.
the cars have been recovered and a case is being opened.
apparently no injuries, all those involved are still being checked by amb. personnel. material damage to both vehicles.
the emergency services are on their way to a traffic accident between two cars in srkedalsveien. unknown extent of damage as of now.
the bus has regained speed and the road is open to normal traffic.
grorudveien between grorudsenter and grorud train station. bus with stops. probably because of the slippery road. blocks the road and creates traffic challenges.

a bus is standing across the road in the galgeberg/normannsgata area. creates traffic challenges. the police are on the scene to direct traffic.drive carefully and be considerate in traffic this afternoon.
then the traffic rolls slowly upwards from skulleruddumpa in one lane, two out of three wagon trains have been chained.
the bus has got a chain and has managed to move on.

e6 exiting at the bottom of the skullerud dump, wagon trains that cannot get forward due to slippery road surface. complete standstill in traffic. contractor with salt is on the way together with the police and tow truck.
ravnkollbakken next to romss centre, bus stops. creates some traffic challenges.
a trailer will be stuck and the driver is putting on a chain in solbrveien. smooth on the spot. the trailer must block traffic in whole or in part. the streetcar is also on its way.

the police held a traffic control in connection with the traffic through the oslofjord tunnel.focus on intoxication and speed.57 checked, of which driver's license seized after km/h in a zone and fines issued on the spot. no one under the influence of drugs.
one driver was taken for a check-up at the health service. both cars have material damage. one of the cars is said to have skidded into the opposite direction, where it collided with an oncoming car.
we are on the scene and in contact with those involved. appears unharmed.
the emergency services on their way to griniveien, cars face to face. undetermined extent of damage, but probably only material damage. queuing must be expected.
arriving at the scene, the fire service can establish that there is only smoke in connection with cooking. what was on the menu is unknown.
the emergency services on their way to vestli. report of smoke from apartment.
car removed, traffic going as normal.
police and tow truck on site.
all traffic is now running as normal.
passenger car with a stop just below the sinsen junction in the direction of storo, westbound. police and tow truck on their way to assist. queuing must be expected.
e18 exit at sjlyst, bus towards car. only material damage and those involved are taken care of on the spot. increased traffic on site, but flow past in the left lane out of town.
the car has been recovered and traffic can flow as normal.
e18 westbound: car w/ stop at the exit to sandvika. we are on site, tow truck on the way.
the event is coming to an end. only a few jumps left. sunday has been very calm and nice for the police and all other actors. welcome home to those of you who are still in holmenkollen.
suspicion of possible drunken driving on one driver. we are opening a case, and the driver's license has been confiscated.

two people are taken to the emergency room for further examinations. must be a violation of the obligation to give way at a roundabout. both cars had material damage that required them to be salvaged.
a police patrol came across a traffic accident in fossumveien. collision from the side. both airbags have deployed, but the people involved appear to be uninjured.

the kollen sunday is here, in glorious weather! the police are betting that this will be a great day with a focus on skiing and a good atmosphere along the slopes. together with all actors, the police will ensure that this will be a safe and good family day in and around holmenkollen!
the fire service now has control of the fire, which probably started in a box of lighter briquettes. no one has been injured.
we are on the scene. there is a lot of smoke inside and residents have started to evacuate themselves. people have so far been evacuated.
all emergency services on their way to ellen gleditsch road at stovner. report of a fire in a terraced house.
the operational effort has been reduced. the case is being investigated further.
the incident leads to stoppages / delays on the subway

the police are at tyen subway. one person suffered stab wounds. the extent of the damage is unknown, but it appears serious. the person is taken to hospital.we are looking for several perpetrators who left the scene.
the car has been recovered and is out of the tunnel.
skuitunnelen direction north: car with stop. the right field is closed.
we have finished on site, the road is open and the cars have been removed. the accident occurred when a car rammed into the car in front.
the emergency services are at a traffic accident on stre aker vei. both lanes are blocked in the northbound direction, due to a leak from one of the vehicles.
the police effort in holmenkollen is now considerably reduced.
the area at frognerseteren is about to be emptied of people. a number of law enforcement missions and drunken people there this afternoon, but everything actually went pretty well.
the fire is extinguished. no one was injured and the police are opening a case.
lots of smoke from an apartment in bjrndal. residents have evacuated themselves. possibly a washing machine on fire.

the -mile is over, and the audience from the arena area is on its way out of the area. there are still many people in the frognerseteren area. there is a high alcohol intake here. several young people are heavily intoxicated, and are taken care of by health. parents should follow up with their hopefuls throughout the afternoon

it is approaching the start of the -mil. the crowd flow is good, and there are reports of a very good atmosphere on the slopes. no significant missions for the police so far. we guide and ensure that the event runs without unwanted incidents.
the train managed to pull over to the side of the road and all lanes are then open to traffic. the police are now on the scene and are making contact with the driver.
train that has stopped in the middle lane on the e6 inbound at abilds. comes on a bit quickly.

we have removed an intoxicated and drunk person from a hotel in the city centre. upon closer inspection, two knives were found which we are confiscating. the person will be reported for carrying a knife in a public place and will also be expelled from the area.

holmenkollen skifest is underway! we hope this will be a brilliant day. the setting is perfect, with sun and lots of people on their way to the field. look after each other, and create a good atmosphere for the athletes throughout the day.
the driver is reported and has his driver's license temporarily confiscated.
one of our patrols has stopped a car where the driver is suspected of being under the influence of drugs. the driver is taken to the emergency department for further examinations.
traffic is flowing well again at the site. case is created.
krysset fagerheimgata/christian michelsensgate, the emergency services are on their way to a traffic accident. cars involved. indicates material damage. may cause traffic problems for a short period.
a driver lost his license after a speeding violation on the e18. the person was measured at km/h in the zone.
the cars have been recovered, and traffic is moving as normal again.
traffic flows past in the left lane, but both cars must be recovered. the police have seized the driver's license of one of the parties, and the police are opening a case.

the emergency services are in the bjrnegrdstunnel, direction north where there has been a traffic accident between two cars. no personal injury, but some material damage. bilberger is requisitioned. traffic passes slowly in the left lane.

the vehicle has been recovered and the road is clear again. the police have questioned a driver who does not have a driver's license. a report will therefore be created for driving without a valid driving licence.
vehicle stop in festningstunnelen, direction east. the car is in the left lane with the police warning. the traffic passes calmly by the place.
it turns out that it is a well-cooked pizza, and the resident receives a health check. the police are opening a case.
the emergency services on their way to a report of smoke development in an apartment block. no flames were observed, and the residents have begun to evacuate themselves.

the police have stopped an excessively drunk driver on the e18 slependen. it took two more patrols to shut the car in before the driver stopped. prepared for blood sampling. no accident or personal injury related to the drive.

the emergency services are at hauketo due to smoke from apartment buildings.5 people have been evacuated from the building.the fire service is working to locate and stop the cause of smoke build-up in the building structure.
the car has been removed and the road has been opened to free traffic
correction: outgoing field for the vehicle punch.
we are on the e18 inbound at sandvika ifb. a vehicle stop in the left field. bilberger has been notified and is on his way. there will be quite a queue at the site.
trondheimsveien by sinsen. traffic accident between cars. major material damage to both cars. no injuries, but one driver was arrested as we suspected drunken/intoxicated driving.
we are with several patrols at an address in lrenveien following a report that a person threatened one or more people with a knife. we now have control of the suspect. no one was physically injured.
the car and the moped have been removed from the roadway - traffic is moving as normal. we open a case and seize the driver's license due to suspected violation of the right of way.
after further investigations by an ambulance at the scene, the driver of the moped is taken to hospital. the extent of damage beyond this is unknown.

the emergency services are in dag hammarskjlds vei regarding a traffic accident between a car and a motorcycle. no serious injuries reported. the driver of the motorbike is taken care of by health on site.

the cyclist has been taken to the emergency room, possible rib fracture. we drive the bike to the owner's home.preliminary information indicates that the parties have been driving in the same direction and that the accident occurred when the driver turned left. we are filing a case on the relationship.

we are with the ambulance in bestumveien on vker following a report of a traffic accident involving a motorist and a cyclist.the cyclist is eventually taken to the emergency room, appears conscious with pain in the upper body. we are working to clarify the sequence of events.

today, women's day is marked with a train in central oslo. the police are also present this year to ensure the safe execution of the events.the events result in further reduced traffic in central oslo. road users are asked to be aware of this.
material damage only. the road is open to normal traffic.
kristian augusts street. we are on our way to a traffic accident. car versus tram. there must not be serious personal injury.

the missing person has now been found by crews from forf.she was found in stmarka and according to the conditions is in good condition. she is being cared for by health now. we thank all the crews from forf for their very good effort and help.
description of the woman: years old, norwegian, fair skinned, moss green down coat, mustard yellow hat, suede uggs. in case of observation: call the police on tel. .
a search is underway for a missing woman in the area of dal brenna and stmarka. we use police patrols, police helicopter, police drones and crews from forf. she has been missing since today.

we have control of a car and driver on ryen after a car tried to get out of control. the car was stopped after a short time and we got control of the driver. the driver has been arrested and is suspected of driving under the influence and several violations of the road traffic act.

the road has been cleared and is open to normal traffic. both drivers have been taken to the emergency department for further examinations. not critically damaged. one of the drivers has the status of being charged with driving under the influence of alcohol, and has had his driver's license confiscated.
the temporary detour will be via bveien/bdalen until further notice.
due to a lot of fallout in the roadway, the road will be closed for a short period. tow truck is on its way.

traffic accident between two cars on rykenveien, by fabrikkdammen. the road is completely closed until further notice. the extent of the damage is unclear, but the people involved must be up and running.

police patrol has control of the lorry driver, following reports from other road users about erratic driving and near misses. the driver is well intoxicated and is produced for the necessary sampling/evidence securing.
the patient is taken to ullevl hospital. the train driver and other affected persons are taken care of.

the emergency services are on the scene. the extent of the damage has not been determined, but the person who was hit is alive. the extent of the damage is not known. the person hit has been pulled forward from the train and is now receiving first aid.
the emergency services are at oslo s after a report that a person has been hit by a train.
in connection with a diesel leak from a vehicle, the road in hoffsveien is slippery. the police and fire brigade are on the scene and the norwegian environmental agency has been notified.
breigata. notification of damage to parked cars. we have searched for relevant persons without results. we have so far found two damaged vehicles.

the police traffic corps has carried out a small traffic control in filipstad. a car driver was stopped and tested positive for the use of drugs. he is driven in for a blood sample. he is reported for the relationship.
the police have finished at the scene and will open a case into the accident. as it now appears, this concerns a breach of the duty to give way. no personal injury and no need for car towing.
the police are at the brumsveien/kirkeveien roundabout where there has been a small traffic accident between two cars. no personal injury. traffic regulation on site, but there is no queue formation.
the two men had been arguing about money, and it ended in a small fight. no serious injury. the police have finished on the scene.
the police have finished the check. a case of driving under the influence has been opened, and the driver's license has been confiscated.
the police are on their way to a bingo in trondheimsveien where there has been a fight between two people. security guards at the site have taken control of both.
the police received a tip from an employee at a pub about two drunken guests who got into a car and drove away. we found the car again and its driver blew a breathalyser above the legal limit.
we have got the person off track. he is not physically injured. the subway can soon resume normal operation over carl berner.

we are at carl berner subway station where a person is standing in the track and does not want to move for the subway. we are in dialogue with the person.because of this, the subway is closed in both directions at carl berner until further notice.

.hanshaugen we are on the scene in casparis gate together with the fire service and ambulance, following a report of dry boils in an apartment. we have control on site. a man has been checked by health personnel, but does not require further follow-up.
two people have been arrested in the case. the victim is being treated in hospital with critical injuries.
haakon viis gate. person knocked down. unconscious. ambulance is on site.
car stopped for inspection on the e6 inbound due to aggressive driving behaviour. driver blew over the legal value of alcohol. driven to the detention center for further testing.
several people in a fight in a restaurant. a person is supervised by paramedics on site. a person who ran from the scene has been taken into custody. he is arrested.
no fire at the address. the fire brigade smelled their way to a barbecue on the roof terrace.
the emergency services are on their way to mrtelverksbakken, report of fire and smoke on a roof. not sure if it's burning, or if it's from a grill.
we have not arrested anyone in the case, but we have a lot of information to go on. probably a relationship between the parties here.
the stalled car has been removed from the roadway. traffic is moving as normal.
the police are in the trosterud area following reports that a person has been robbed using a knife.
the fire brigade is on the scene and gives warnings until recovery is on the scene.
e18 direction drammen before the exit to asker. car with a stop in the left lane. this one comes on quickly. drive carefully.

finally, the car that was lying on its side has been removed.it took longer than expected due to both traffic and the fact that the car was in a knotty position for the tow truck. the car owner writes the damage report himself.

the bus is struggling to turn around at the end stop at barlindbekken/trettestykket because many people have parked there incorrectly.we have notified the municipality, which will consider measures (read: fines) against the wrongly parked cars.

we are in contact with the driver. no injuries have been reported and as of now we have no information on the cause either, but that is something we are working to clarify.solliveien is at least completely blocked until further notice.

a car has ended up on its side in solliveien a few km below solli. this means that traffic cannot pass either upwards or downwards until the car has been removed from the site. the tow truck is on its way, the matter will hopefully be resolved in half an hour.
at the bottom of maridalsveien, we stopped a car driver who, after further investigation, appears to be intoxicated. he is therefore taken to the detention center for sample collection.
we are done on the spot. no injuries in connection with the incident.
the emergency services are on their way to nyjordet where a car fire has been reported. according to the report, there must be a risk of spreading to other vehicles.
we have ended the operational effort. the case continues in the investigation track.
the victim is not seriously injured. followed up by health. we have an ongoing search for the perpetrators. no one has yet been arrested.
we have responded to a report of a stabbing near birkelunden. we are in contact with an offended party who has injuries to a shoulder.
no fire on site. only some fault in an electrical system.
the emergency services are on their way to an address in kirkeveien, report of a fire. uncertain extent.
according to the fire service, this is not dramatic. small fire in an apartment, no people exposed to an abnormal amount of smoke.
the emergency services are on their way to fagerborggata, report of a fire in an apartment. uncertain extent.
e18 hjortnes has been cleared and opened to traffic. traffic will gradually return to normal. we open a case.
this is under hjortneslokkett.

on the e18 westbound, we have received a report of a traffic accident. possible talk of being hit from behind. no serious injuries reported. this leads to queues. emergency services on their way to the scene.
we are on our way to treskeveien. probably a dry boil there, and no fire. some smoke in the area, but according to the fire service, it should no longer burn.
the car has now been removed from the tunnel. thus, there should be no danger of the "taco friday" falling apart. there is still some queue left, but it clears up in a short time.
car with a stop in the vlereng tunnel, direction city centre. the car is parked in the left lane, creating long queues to the rear. salvage is underway.
more patrols sent to oslo s after a report that a person was in possession of a gun. no person shall be directly threatened. we quickly got control of the man. he was arrested and a gun was seized.
the fire service carries out subsequent extinguishing throughout the evening and probably at night. we open a case.
obre has good control, but work is being done on the storey partition, which still has a high temperature.

the fire service reports that they have put the fire down, but not under control. work is underway to investigate whether the fire has spread in the building structure. we have control over the two in the apartment who are being taken to the emergency room for a check-up.
flames and smoke have been reported from an apartment on the fourth floor. several have evacuated from the building. the fire is currently not under control.
the emergency services are on their way to mllergata where a fire has been reported in a building.
the road is cleared and open. we have questioned the driver and the driver's license has been confiscated. case is created.
e16 outbound just before the skuitunnelen, a car has driven into the barrier for the road service. major damage to the car and the road is closed past the scene, local diversion.
the emergency services and tow trucks are now on site. the police are opening a case into the accident.

the emergency services are in durudveien where there has been a traffic accident. a car has collided with two parked cars. a woman has been taken to hospital for further follow-up. the cause of the accident currently appears to be a case of illness. bilberger req for salvage of cars.

the emergency services are in frysjaveien where there has been a work accident on a construction site. a worker has fallen and suffered a serious leg injury. the worker has been taken to hospital. the police carry out a crime scene investigation and information gathering at the scene.
ring has been opened and we are opening a case on the relationship. we have seized the driver's license of the driver we suspect drove into the other car from behind.
one person has been driven okl, while the other person is uninjured. car recovery is ongoing, and for a short period the road will be closed during this work.

a person needs the supervision of an ambulance for pain in the neck. bilberger is requisitioned. this creates a lot of traffic in the area, and especially in the eastbound direction, between smestad and ullevl.
the police are on their way to ring , between smestad and ullevl where there has been a traffic accident between cars. we do not know the extent as of now. creates some queue in the area.
the vehicles have been removed from e6 now. free movement. we take the parties off the motorway to record explanations. no personal injury reported.

on the e6 inbound at alnabru there has been a collision between a car and a truck. information from the site may indicate that there has been a field change. no serious injuries have been reported. the two middle fields are closed. the emergency services are on their way to the scene.
the car has been removed. we are opening a case on the matter and the driver's license has been confiscated. driver taken over by health.
salvage has collected the car with a stop. the road is open and traffic is moving as normal.

e18 in the direction of drammen, there is a car that has been stopped. the car is in the right lane just before the exit to sandvika. this has led to queues, but the traffic flows slowly past. we are on site and give alerts until recovery is on site.
in fossumveien near stovner centre, our patrol came across a single accident where a car has driven into a snowdrift. the ambulance checks out the driver of the car.
e6 v/ sandstuveien is open and morning traffic runs as normal.
the tow truck is in place and begins work to remove the wagon train. there is still slow-moving traffic at the site. traffic will slowly but surely return to normal.
e6 towards oslo v/ exit sandstuveien. wagon train with a stop. blocks right field. the police are on the scene, a tow truck is on its way.
the girl is safe and sound.
the police have control over three people, including the two injured.the case is being investigated further.
the police are at haugen regarding a violent incident. two people have cut/stabbing injuries. both have been taken to hospital with serious but not life-threatening injuries.

we are looking for a girl who is missing. she may be in oslo. possibly together with a friend. description: years, -165 cm tall, -55 kg. short auburn hair, burgundy red hoodie, light blue trousers. possibly wearing a black jacket.
the car has been recovered and all lanes are open again.
the car is off the road and all lanes are open to traffic.
talk about a car with the engine stopped, work is being done to salvage the car now. slow moving queue past the place.
e18 exit at vker; car that has stopped in the middle lane. bilberger is on his way. arrives a little too soon, and there is a queue behind from oslo.
talk about a minor traffic accident between a lorry and a car, only material damage. the road is cleared.
the driver has moved on.
a car and a lorry have stopped on the e18 in the outbound direction where the approach from the granfoss tunnel exits onto the e18. police and tow truck on the way.
the car got away before we arrived, the road is open again.
some candles and lighters were found in the bushes, we are opening a case.
a person is changing tires on the e134 in an easterly direction at the exit to hyggenveien. the police are on their way.
a car is in the right lane in the eastbound direction. the police and tow truck are on their way.
a car has had its engine stop in the right lane on the e6 outbound just before the exit to furuset. the police and tow truck are on their way and the car will be removed as soon as possible.
we are done on the spot. a car driver went to the emergency room for a check-up due to pain in a foot. we are filing a case on the relationship. two motorists had their driving licenses confiscated.
police and fire service are in paal bergs vei in bogerud where there has been a fire in a hedge. there were no injuries and the hedge burned itself out.
chain collision on the e6 exit at furuset. three cars are in the left lane. no report of personal injury. car recovery is on its way.
the car has been recovered. the parties write a damage report.
three cars involved, and as mentioned no injuries. salvage is requested for a car. traffic is being diverted at the scene.
on rykenveien, just south of the junction to bleikerveien: we are on our way to a traffic accident. undetermined extent of damage, but probably no injuries.
a kick-cyclist and a tram have had a collision at jernbanetorget. the kick-cyclist is up and is considered to be slightly injured - taken to emergency room.
tvetenveien. we are in the area around the mix kiosk where an incident is said to have occurred inside the kiosk. talk about an aggressive person who has now left the place.
car slid down slope. person in the car. the person is awake, the fire service is working to get the person out of the car and up the slope. all emergency services are on site.
we have removed nine protesters from the entrance area. these did not comply with the police's orders. they are reported for this.
ministry of finance, akersgata. at the request of dss, we are working to remove protesters from the entrance area so that employees can get to work.
the load on the roof was not secured. no other vehicles were hit when the load fell off. the driver is reported and has had his driver's license temporarily confiscated.
the car and load have been removed from the roadway. the tunnel is reopened in both fields.
vlerengtunnelen direction towards the city centre: car that has lost some roof load. the vehicle is in the left lane. left field is closed.the police are on their way.
the truck has now been removed from the roadway.
there will be some stoppage in bus traffic while recovery is in progress.
right by skjerven farm. a truck that has a loose trailer/lost. this means that the road has been blocked. tow truck is on its way.
the demonstrators who were inside the barricades did not comply with the police's orders. they have now been carried out by the police.

it has been decided to clear keysers gate between akersgata and munchs gate. this is to ensure that employees have access to their workplace. both requests and orders have been given to the demonstrators to move. they have not complied with this.
the car has now been recovered and all fields are open.
vehicles with a stop just after the exit from the vlereng tunnel, eastbound. salvage on the way. the traffic flows smoothly past.
emergency services on site. no one seriously injured. traffic flows smoothly in one lane.
the emergency services are on their way to a traffic accident in heggedal. the car must be off the road. unclear extent of damage.
all protesters were then removed from the scene and taken to the police station. all have the status of brought in. -50 protesters have also turned up outside the ministry. this also goes smoothly.

the protesters were given a deadline of to leave the building. no one has followed this order, and they are now being brought to the police station by us. the demonstrators offer passive resistance so that we have to carry them away. this goes smoothly and in a controlled manner.
the police have both the right and the duty to comply with such a request. this is a building that is classified as an object worthy of protection.

oslo police district received a request from dss on sunday evening to remove the protesters who have been inside the oil and energy ministry since thursday. we are now on site and have given the protesters an order to leave the site.
traffic accident between a semi-trailer and a car. no personal injury. the tow truck is on its way to the passenger car. the semi-trailer has moved out of the intersection now.
the car has now driven off under its own power.
on the e6 inbound at furuset, approx. on a par with ikea, it's a car that looks a bit awkward in the public transport lane. we have a patrol along the way.
the search for the second man ended negatively. we work at the scene and take care of this.

report about a burglary in an electronics store at lambertseter. we have sent several patrols to the scene, including a dog patrol. a person is apprehended by a police dog. we are looking for another perpetrator who is masked and has run from the scene.
this is a building that is undergoing renovation. no people should live there. the fire is now out. we are investigating the cause of the fire.
we and the fire service are on the scene. kjlberggata will be closed as it is full of emergency vehicles. the fire brigade has started extinguishing.
all emergency services on their way to a report of a fire in an apartment building in kjlberggata. it must burn in the tarpaulin or any building materials that are on the outside of the building.
there was smoke in the apartment and a person received a health check on the spot. the fire brigade has control and starts venting.
we and the fire service are on a dry boil in vibes gate.

no injuries, all involved have been checked by health personnel. collision from behind due to braking. as of now, no information about the car that first braked up, as it is not at the scene. claim reports are filled out.
the emergency services are on their way to a report of a traffic accident between cars in holmlia center road. the extent of the damage is currently unknown, but minor injuries are possible.
we are finished on the spot, an investigation file is created. the fire service has imposed a fire ban on residents.
appears as a warm passage from the pipe to the building mass. the fire service is still working to remove the cladding to check this out.
the fire inlet has been extinguished. the fire brigade ventilates at the address. residents are looked after by health. two people have evacuated themselves.
the emergency services are also on their way to a report of a small fire at an address in bestum.

the fire brigade and the police are in bauneveien after smoke inside a detached house. the fire service is working to remove some wall covering to investigate the cause of the smoke. no injuries have been reported, so far it appears to be undramatic.
the fire is now out. an apartment is totally damaged. no one was physically injured.
the fire service has the fire under control, but it has not been extinguished. people have been evacuated. no one was physically injured.
the fire service is working to gain control, while the evacuation of people is ongoing. as of now, no overview of the extent of the damage.
the emergency services are on their way to roveruds gate where there is a fire in an apartment on the first floor.
the car has been recovered. we have opened a case.
traffic accident where a car has driven off the road and wedged itself between a cliff/rock wall and a house facade. we are in contact with the driver of the car, who is uninjured.
the police have finished on the scene. fire will further investigate where the smoke may have come from.
we are in kernveien following a report of smoke from a training center there has been no fire. visitors have evacuated themselves until further notice.
the cars have been salvaged. one of the drivers is reported for breaching the duty to give way.
the bus has been saved.
traffic is flowing smoothly at the scene of the accident. one of the drivers has neck pain and is taken to the emergency room. bilberger is in the process of recovering the two vehicles.
/brenna we are on our way to a traffic accident at dal-brenna. two cars are said to have collided at an intersection. no report of personal injuries.
towing has been ordered with some waiting time. queue towards the place. traffic passes in the left lane.
a bus with a stop on e6 leaving at skulleruddumpa. must stand on the shoulder of the road now.
police and fire responded to a fire in an apartment in bogstadveien. the resident must have extinguished the fire himself. the cause was a screwed-on hotplate that was left to itself.

the fire brigade has control of the fire. there has been a fire in a block of flats, cause unknown. two people have ingested some smoke and are being monitored by health personnel. a dog is rescued from the main floor of the house.
tow truck is on site.
sjvollbukta. report of fire/smoke from a kitchen in a dormitory apartment.
e . after the sandvika exit. we have stopped a motorist after several callers reacted to his driving behaviour.
two fields will be closed in connection with recovery. the left field is kept open.
the tow truck is now on the scene.
e18 inbound at hvik. wagon train with a stop in the middle field. creates major traffic challenges. tow truck is on its way.
one car will be towed away, and the other car will be moved to the public transport area, so that traffic flows smoothly past the site.
creates queue formation.
e18 inbound at lysaker. traffic accident, hit from behind.
the tyenbadet area. smoke development in a building under construction.
then the bus has moved on and the traffic flows smoothly at smestadkrysset.

in ullernchaussee a few meters before the smestad junction, an articulated bus has stopped. this causes traffic challenges at the intersection, so those who can take alternative routes past the site are advised to do so. tungberger is requisitioned.
the scene of the accident on the loenga bridge was immediately cleared. we are filing a case on the relationship.
the e6 skullerud dump is now open, and traffic is moving as normal.
a motorist has crashed on the loenga bridge after he came driving out of the ekeberg tunnel. the emergency services are on the scene. the driver has been sent to hospital with serious injuries.

the fire service stated that the possible cause of the fire is due to the connection with the pantograph on the roof of the carriage. the fire brigade will remain on the scene for a while. we are filing a case on the relationship.
the suspect is reported for the attempted burglary and the person concerned is expelled from the scene.
the e6 is now temporarily closed at skulleruddumpa southbound due to recovery of the semi-trailer.
a guard saw a man trying to break in a door at storo centre. we have control over the suspect a little off the street now. we are trying to find out what the suspect's plan was.
the tow truck has brought the trailer, and the e134 has been opened to traffic in the direction of drammen again.

a semi-trailer has driven off the road up from skulleruddumpa exiting on the e6. the tractor is well out in the ditch and must be removed by heavy lifters. no personal injury.white roads with snow, also on the main road network, so we have had a few minor traffic accidents so far tonight.

the fire service has disconnected the train carriage in question and brought up a fire train to try to stop the development of smoke. challenges with high voltage associated with the train set mean that the crews must be careful in their approach.

a truck train cannot get up the hill on the e134 towards midtbygda and the chains the driver has with him cannot be put on. that's why tungberger is on its way.traffic in the direction of drammen must use the old road from the elgskaus tunnel until further notice.
we are together with the fire service in lodalen to investigate reports of smoke from a parked train carriage.
e18 is now cleared and there is normal traffic in all lanes.
there will be long queues at the site. traffic is currently passing in one lane. ring is recommended as an alternative driving route.
a person must have been hit by a lorry train on the e18 entering lysaker. the emergency services are on their way to the scene.
e18 is open for normal traffic again.
the accident is just after the exit to asker from the e18, and there is a queue before the scene of the accident. no personal injury. bilberger is on his way.
traffic accident on the e18 exit at asker. provisional notification of major traffic problems. truck and car involved. no information on personal injuries as of now. we are on our way.

we are in evjebakken after reports of a lorry skidding on a slippery road. we can ascertain that it is very slippery on the spot, and ask people to consider other driving routes until it becomes strewn.
bilberger has got the wagon train out of the way and we finish on the spot.
we direct traffic on site, but some queues must be expected. tungberger is on his way.
the rectification wagon train is obstructing the traffic, we are on site and directing the traffic past. tungberger is on his way.
police and rescue service on the way to the e18 outbound between katten and fiskevollbukta.wagon train with a stop. probably not an obstacle to traffic, but blocking parts of the footpath.
the fire brigade has extinguished the fire. somewhat unclear ownership here, but it does not belong to a private address. the police are opening a case.

five young men have been brought into custody to clarify what role they have had in the case. we have not been able to get in touch with the rental company to clarify the rental conditions. the car has been towed in from the site.

the emergency services are on a fire in a detached garage in rnningveien. there is no danger of spreading and the fire service is in the process of extinguishing the fire. cause of fire currently unknown.
a patrol stopped a motorist on majorstua. the driver appeared to be under the influence of drugs and will therefore be taken in for an extended test.

the driver has also crashed into parked cars in nonnegata/myklegardsgata. these have received minor damage. we are working on contacting owners.we are working to clarify who was the driver and how/who rented the car.
picture from the intersection oslo gate x bispegata where the driver drove down a pole at the traffic lights.

a patrol wanted to stop a rental car for a check in bjrvika. the driver did not stop and attempted to evade. he drove down a traffic light pole in oslo gt, before stopping in a fence in vestfoldgata. young men arrested as they tried to run away from the scene.
during the search of the apartment, we also seized an air pistol. victims taken to family, while those arrested have been taken to prison.

food courier who delivered food saw a woman being threatened in an apartment. when the patrol arrived, the woman had taken refuge inside his car. a man stood outside and threatened with an axe.the patrol had to threaten with firearms to get the man to desist from the threat. no one injured.
e6 opened and traffic flows as normal.
there is a thin layer of snow on the main road network this evening which makes it slippery. drive carefully
we are on site. the driver of the car is conscious and does not appear to be seriously injured.
traffic accident on e6 inbound at alnabru. a single accident is reported where a car has hit the guardrail and spun. emergency services on their way to the scene.
no fire in the vehicle. it has now been moved out of the road and traffic is moving as normal.
message about smoke from vehicles. garbage truck probably with hot brakes. blocks nedre kalbakkvei from the center and a little way down the road. car towing is required.
major material damage to the car, driver checked by ambulance at the scene. the car is being salvaged at the time of writing.
the emergency services are on their way to the e18 inbound exit drengsrud, where a car will be driven into the traffic guard.
traffic flows almost as normal towards ryen/manglerud now. somewhat slower all the way towards ryen, but decent flow.
queues towards the site, call westbound at manglerud/ryen if the traffic must be sluiced in one lane.

we have control over three people who will be questioned later in the day about their involvement in the case. they are to be considered suspects as of now. we are done at the scene, but are investigating the matter further.
three people have been arrested at vollebekk. the search for more people involved is still ongoing.
call westbound manglerud. bus with diesel leak. work is underway to clean up the site.

violent incident in an apartment. several fled the scene in a car after gaining access to the apartment. this has been controlled some distance away from the crime scene. no one appears to be seriously injured. we are working to find out what happened
stortingsgata. one person arrested and one expelled after a fight.
car stopped for inspection on rv4 near linderud. driver does not have a driver's license. we also suspect driving under the influence of drugs. driven to the arrest for sampling.

a uniformed police car that was stationary at a red light was hit from behind by another car. this attempted to drive away from the scene, but was stopped after a short time. we suspect that the suspected driver is under the influence of drugs, so an extended test will be taken.

a person has been arrested in romerike in a car that we believe is involved in this case. the police have secured clues linking the person concerned to the incident. he is not injured. he will be taken to the central detention center in oslo.
we have examined a tesla that was parked nearby in the parking lot and we believe that this may have been involved in the case. this is therefore towed in for further investigations.
a person has presented at a hospital and has injuries consistent with being involved in this incident. he is conscious, but the police do not want to specify the extent of the damage further.
we are looking for a dark tesla that may have suffered damage to a tire as a result of shooting. we would like information about this if you have this.

we have information that the car that was shot at drove away from the scene, while another car drove away from the scene in an unknown direction.it is unknown how many people were involved in the incident.

we are at the furuset stadium after a report of shooting at a car in a parking space. we are on the scene and in contact with many witnesses who have called the police emergency number.we are currently not in contact with anyone who has been involved in the incident itself.

two people have been arrested and a third person is also to be arrested. a man has been taken to hospital for treatment with injuries that are not as serious as we initially feared.the incident started outside nav at the top of thorvald meyers gate and we stopped it at lilleborg church.
the police are present in the area with many patrols. we are working to obtain information from witnesses. parallel to this, a search is underway for several people who may be involved.
the police currently have control over four people. one person has what appear to be stab/impact injuries. he is being treated by paramedics. he is conscious but seriously injured.
the police are in the torshov and sagene area after reports of a fight. we are looking for more people involved. as of now, the extent of the damage is unclear.

traffic accident between motorist and cyclist in the roundabout at shell in etterstad. the cyclist appears uninjured. the driver of the car is reported for the relationship, and has his driver's license confiscated.
the road has been cleared, and all lanes are open to normal traffic.
two of the cars are drivable. the other two are in the process of being loaded onto a tow truck now. the road will open soon.
before the complaints come. we are of course in asker.
e18 entering bellevuedumpa. traffic accident involving four vehicles. the sequence of events and the extent of the damage are currently unclear. major problems with traffic management.
no serious injury. all those involved were expelled from the scene.
several people involved in a fight at karl johan. one person is bleeding from the head and will be attended to by an ambulance.

we finish on the spot and file a case. the fire may have started in connection with a wine cabinet inside a storeroom.several apartments have to be washed due to smoke and the residents involved have been notified of this.

the ambulance has now got an overview of the extent of the damage, and the man in the fire apartment is being taken to hospital after inhaling smoke. the woman was in the apartment before being taken to the emergency room for treatment. emergency services are still working at the scene.
the fire service reports that the fire has been extinguished and that they have started ventilation. no injuries have been reported, but an ambulance is on the scene.

we are working to get an overview of those who have been evacuated. for now, we have control over the most important apartments; the fire apartment and those above. the police have an assembly area for evacuees on the outside where we are working to get an overview.
those who were in the apartment where the fire started have been evacuated from the building. the fire alarm goes off in the entire block and several people have evacuated the building.

the emergency services are at an address in rustadgrenda when we received a report of a fire at the site. there will be black smoke coming out of a window on the nd floor. we have just arrived at the scene and the fire brigade is starting a search.

we are looking for a man (56) who left brum hospital at pm. he may have gone home to heggedal/heggeodden, but he is not at home.he is cm tall, thin, wearing a thick blue bubble jacket and dark trousers (possibly sweatpants). he has short light gray hair.

we have spoken to the patient at the hospital. we open a case.so far, there are many indications that he has been hit in a pedestrian crossing and that the driver who did this drove away from the scene without speaking to the patient or contacting the emergency services.

the patient may have been hit while crossing a pedestrian crossing at solvang kolonihager. he is taken to hospital for further treatment.we have not been contacted by any witnesses who have information in the case, but we would very much like further information in the case.

investigations at the scene indicate that this was a rear-end collision. the accident happened when the leading car was about to turn off from ljabruveien. the driver of the rear car has had his license confiscated.
the cars have been removed from the roadway - traffic is moving as normal. we are still on site and investigating.

police and ambulance are in contact with a man who was hit while crossing sognsveien. he does not appear seriously injured.the driver who did this drove away. we are looking for the car involved, as well as speaking to witnesses at the scene.

on ljabruveien x mortensrudveien by hauketo. two cars have been in a traffic accident. we are on site. person appears to be slightly injured, that person is being looked after by health. as of now, one field is closed
the car has been removed from the e18 and traffic is moving as normal.
the police are on the scene. the car is in the driveway. there is a slow-moving queue in two lanes. we are waiting for a tow truck.
e18 right after asker in the direction of drammen. car stopped after the collision from solbr. we and the tow truck are on our way.
the emergency services are ready at the scene. there must have been a fire in a freezer on the veranda. we open a case

the person who was inside the apartment, which is located on romss, is out and receiving treatment from the ambulance. there is still smoke in the hallway, but reports from the first units on the scene are that the fire on the balcony has been extinguished.
all emergency services are on their way to a fire in an apartment in oddvar solbergsvei. there will be a fire on a balcony on the st floor. a good deal of smoke on site.
the car is then recovered and the e18 outbound is now opened to normal traffic in all lanes.

we have now started car recovery of the car that is in danger of sliding down the e . the e18 outbound is blocked in the right lane. only heavy vehicles are allowed to drive in the left lane. passenger cars are diverted to and from the e18, via sandviksveien. e18 input works as normal. this will take -60 min
the car will be salvaged soon. then e18 outbound will be closed. we will provide an update when e18 is closed.

we are in bjerkoddveien together with the fire service and ambulance in connection with a car that has skidded. the car is now secured by the fire service. the driver of the car is supervised by an ambulance. the person has back pain.
it is then open to normal traffic again. one person is slightly injured. the person was treated by an ambulance at the scene. we are filing a case on the relationship.

we and the ambulance are in vestre haugen, furuset on a construction site after a report of an occupational accident. one person is seriously but not critically injured. this must have happened in connection with the renovation of apartments on site.
we and an ambulance are in alf bjercke's road following a report of a traffic accident between cars. some material damage. undetermined extent of damage to the persons.
the car has run into a power pole. are very difficult driving conditions on site. lots of slush on the road.
sheimveien. traffic accident notification. must be a single accident. we are in dialogue with the driver.
both vehicles have now been removed and traffic is moving as normal.
the fire must now be extinguished using fire extinguishers.
police and fire brigade on their way to an address in enebakkveien after reports of a fire in a rubbish bin.
police on the scene. a total of people involved in two vehicles. one person appears slightly injured. major material damage to the vehicles.
traffic accident at circle k on abilds. two cars involved. the emergency services are on their way to the scene.
we are at an address in connection with a serious domestic disturbance. there are two people with minor injuries. a fire extinguisher in the hallway has also been emptied.
should be talking about dry boiling. no one has been evacuated.
verksgata. we are on our way to a report of a fire in an apartment.

mortensrud t lane. we have arrested two people who had tried to get in to the subway driver. one person is being reported for harassment and violence against a public official. another person who interfered with the police's work is reported for the same.

hans nielsens hauges gate. we are looking for a person who we suspect has committed a break-in at a car repair shop. the suspect is seen running from the scene. description: man, black clothes, black buff, white soles on shoes, fair skin, tall and thin.
the fire alarm has been reset. the fire brigade will remain on the scene for a while longer. dry boiling can be a possible cause, where the smoke has then spread upwards in the ventilation system.
it is still unclear what caused the smoke. a total of people were exposed to smoke. emergency services are still on the scene.
the smoke is subsiding. not yet located where it originally came from. a total of three people are said to have been exposed to smoke. these are checked by health on site.
lybekkergata at the end of hammersborggata is closed due to the ladder truck for the fire service.
smoke development from a ventilation system on the th floor. evacuation is ongoing, and the whole of oslo city will be evacuated.
the emergency services have received a report of smoke developing in a ventilation system in oslo city. the fire brigade is on the scene.
we have stopped a motorist whose driver does not have a valid driver's license. driving under the influence of drugs is suspected. we opened a case.

we have control over a person who has broken a window at burger king majorstua. we are also in contact with witnesses who saw the incident. the reasons why the suspect smashed the window are not known. being reported for damage.

water intrusion has been reported in nos. , , and . not living rooms. the fire brigade and oslo municipality are working on the scene. there is currently no need for residents to evacuate. not sure when the water will be back on.
ivinds vei is blocked between no. and .
oslo water and wastewater has been notified and is on its way to the site.
the fire brigade reports a major water leak in the ivinds vei area of rvoll. probable water line break. for the time being, there has been a report of water seeping into the basement at one address.
rykenveien is now open in both directions.
rykenveien direction asker center is now open.
the accident probably happened as a result of a disabled vehicle running a red light. the driver of this is slightly injured.
rykenveien is per now completely closed in both directions.
rykenveien/bleikerveien intersection. traffic accident. a person in a disabled vehicle hit by a car. there must not be serious personal injury. the emergency services are on their way to the scene.
as a result of the traffic accident in lier, it is not possible to drive the e134 between ryken/midtbygda and lierstranda.detour until further notice rv167 heggedal/asker from e134 ryken.

the child who was hit has now been pronounced dead at the scene. this appears to be a tragic accident where those involved are family. these are taken care of by health resources and the police both on site and further afield.
the emergency services are at a traffic accident in hvik where a child has been hit inside a garage. we are in contact with relatives on the spot.
after a report of a woman who screamed and disturbed the night peace in the gjvikgata area, we came into contact with a woman in her s. she was taken into custody.
probably a small pipe fire that went out by itself before we got to work.
police and fire service are on scene in korsgata in connection with a report of a fire in an apartment building. the fire service is investigating. korsgata is currently closed.
we travel from the location. case is created.
the merraskott tunnel is open to normal traffic.
the merraskott tunnel is currently closed in both directions.
we and the fire service are between the oslofjord tunnel and the merraskott tunnel, where a car has caught fire. the fire is extinguished. no one injured. probably started to burn while driving.

the road is again open to normal traffic. the incident occurred in connection with a lane change where a car was hit by a lorry. we open a case and the driver of the lorry has his driving license temporarily confiscated.
traffic is currently passing by in two lanes. will be closed during salvage.

the emergency services are on the scene. it appears that no one is seriously injured. some material damage to vehicles. probably a passenger car that has spun and driven into a guard rail. there has also been a rear-end collision due to cars slowing down due to the accident.
e6 inbound at alnabru. traffic accident notification. several cars must be involved. unknown extent of damage. the emergency services are on their way to the scene.
car stopped on rv4 due to speed. it turned out that it was affixed with identification marks belonging to another vehicle. we also suspect that the driver is under the influence of drugs.

major material damage to the two cars, so towed away. the accident has occurred when a driver has driven against the direction of travel up and out of the upper level. the other accidentally hit the gas hard and crashed into the other car and the wall. the latter has been deprived of his driver's license.

a driver has crashed with one or more other cars in the car park at trekanten. no injuries, but two cars had to be towed from the scene. we are talking to witnesses and suspects to find out why this happened.
we have left the scene and are opening a case on the matter.
we have clarified the identity of the injured man and next of kin have been notified. he is being treated in hospital and is being followed up there.

the driver of the wheel loader has been taken to hospital for treatment. the accident occurred in connection with work on site, so the norwegian labor inspection authority has been notified. we are still working on investigations at the scene.

the emergency services are at hovseter following a report that a small wheel loader has tipped over on its side. the driver is conscious, but is in pain and is therefore being treated by the ambulance.

the person has been taken to hospital for treatment. he is seriously injured. we currently have no further details on the course of events. we are still working on site with technical investigations.if you have information on the case, contact the police.
an injured person has been found outdoors in frysja. police and ambulance are on the scene. undetermined extent of damage and course of events.
the girl has recovered.
the fire in the shed has been extinguished. we do not know the cause at this time. case is created.
the emergency services are on their way to sjstrand after reports of a fire in a shed.
the cars have been towed away. two of those involved were taken onward for a health check. we are done on the spot.
there is a queue towards ryen, from the south. traffic passes the accident site, but at a slow speed.
traffic accident on the e6 inbound at ryen. three cars involved. three out of four lanes are blocked, queuing at the site. no report of personal injury.
the truck has been towed to a more suitable location. normal traffic.
the emergency services are on their way to a report of a fire in bhusveien in oslo. some residents have evacuated themselves. it is unclear whether it is dry boiling or a fire.
a lorry has been stopped in the right lane on the e6 exit at ulvensplitten. traffic flows smoothly in other fields.
traffic accident at the intersection uranienborgveien/ parkveien. two motorists who have collided. bilberger is on his way. must not be personal injury.
the car has been recovered and the road is open to traffic.the contractor is on site to sprinkle as it is slippery on site.the driver of the car has been checked out by health personnel.

ravnkollbakken: traffic accident between a car and a truck. relatively low speed. appears to be minor damage to the driver of the car. police and ambulance are on the scene.the vehicles are moved as soon as possible to open up traffic. tow truck is on its way.
we are on the scene and the fire service has started extinguishing.
we and the fire brigade have moved to karl johansgate in connection with a fire in rubbish associated with the renovation of a building. a risk of spreading to the building has been reported.
the road is cleared. the car has not been in the tunnel wall, but stopped a few cm earlier. the driver says he is acutely ill and had to stop immediately. followed up by health.
e16 entering the bjrnegrd tunnel, a car has hit the tunnel wall at low speed. a person in the car who is supervised by an ambulance. traffic passes in a field past the site.
the fire service has investigated the scene and it appears to be only coolant. we are waiting for tow trucks to remove the bus.

the fire brigade and we are in sognsveien directly above sogn vgs after a bus has been stopped and diesel leaked. the fire brigade is in the process of collecting it, some traffic challenges past the site.
the incident is being investigated and we are reviewing the information obtained. as of now, we have not come into contact with anyone we can link to the incident.
the premises are secured via a security company and we have finished the search in the area. no one has been arrested for the burglary.
the police are in rudssletta where there has been a burglary in a commercial premises. a window that gives access to the room has been broken. we are searching the area for the perpetrator.

this appears to be a basket roof where the injured person is subjected to violence by two young men. these had left the scene before the police/amb arrived at the scene. all the time we haven't received any information from the injured person, we can say little for sure about the course of events as of now.

.hanshaugen police and amb have moved out to waldemar thranes gate. a man is subjected to violence and has a stab wound. he was awake and conscious when he was taken to hospital. we are in the area with a number of units, searching for clues and people who may have information about the incident.

report about a car that varied greatly in speed and that wobbled on the e18 entering asker. stopped and controlled. it turned out that the striking driving behavior was due to a lack of competence behind the wheel. the -year-old driver was alone in the car.
we are done on the spot. a case will be opened for burglary, possession of drugs and carrying a knife in a public place.
three people caught red-handed after breaking into the basement premises of a business. the police are on the scene with two patrols.
we will contact you when we find the owner of the mobile phones.when you report, we want to know the imei number of the phone, among other things, so that we can more easily find the owner.
a patrol responded to the speed of a driver on ring . it turned out that he was drunk, so he is taken in for sampling.
we have received many reports of such mobile phone thefts in recent weeks.if you haven't reported the theft yet, you can easily do so at .

in the last two nights, detectives have arrested two pickpockets who have apparently specialized in stealing mobile phones on the dance floor of nightclubs in the city centre.we have found around stolen mobile phones which we are working to find the owner of.
no one has been arrested and we have opened a case on behalf of the victim.

we have had a traffic control on mosseveien leaving at ulvya.one drove without a valid driver's license and appeared to be under the influence of drugs, so he will be presented to a doctor.another initially blew above the legal value, but ended up short of the evidence protection.
the cause appears to be a traffic dispute with disagreement and honking before the other party hit the taxi driver. we are not in contact with any suspects yet.

we and the ambulance are in contact with a taxi driver who is exposed to violence in torggata. he is eventually taken to the emergency department for treatment. he does not appear seriously injured.we are looking for a suspect who is wearing light jeans and a black hoodie.
a man punched and kicked parked cars, and he broke a window in a cafe. he is too drunk to take care of himself, so he is taken to the detention center.
a man broke a window or similar in a night club, so he was expelled from the place. it was too much for him to comply with, so now he is being taken to the detention center.

the police received a report of a person with cuts at the emergency room. he was driven there by car. it is unclear what happened in advance, but everything indicates that the crime scene is somewhere else. the victim is awake and conscious.
the girl has now been found by her mother.
the police are looking for a little girl aged . she was last seen in the vre slottsgate area. she is wearing a pink tracksuit, flowered purple boots. without outer jacket. tips call .
we are creating an investigation into the relationship.
the fire has been extinguished, but some light smoke remains at the scene.
police and the fire service are on their way to a report of a fire in a garage belonging to a detached house. possible from one fridge. residents of the detached house have evacuated themselves.
no trace of people on board the boat. uncertain reason why the boat went down.
police and the fire service are on their way to a report about a fishing boat that went down during the night. the fire brigade has divers on their way.
the fire probably started in an older truck. we are filing a case on the relationship.

we are with the fire service in lkkafossen following reports of a fire in an outbuilding/barracks in an industrial area. not reported on persons involved. we are trying to get in touch with witnesses at the scene.
we have had a blood alcohol check at e18 filipstad. of approximately drivers checked, two were reported for drink-driving. one of them also lost his driver's license.
two people whom we arrested close to the crime scene have been arrested and taken into custody.two victims have been taken to the emergency room with minor injuries.

we are in contact with two offended men, these are being examined by the ambulance. they do not appear to have serious injuries to their faces, but the extent of the damage has not been clarified.we are in contact with several others involved, whose roles we are working to clarify.
we are in klingenberggata after reports of a fight involving several people.no one appears seriously injured, but we are investigating information that a knife or similar has been involved.

correction: this is not a serious incident. the first report here was about a stabbing. no one has been stabbed, but there has been an incident of violence between several people. no one is seriously injured, and no one wants treatment by an ambulance.
.hanshaugen the emergency services are in the fredensborgveien area. here there must have been a traffic accident, and that a basket roof has occurred afterwards. not sure if anyone was injured.
the vehicles involved have now been removed from the road, and traffic is flowing as normal again.

the driver of the car involved is taken to hospital for treatment. she is awake and aware.the sequence of events is currently unclear. the emergency services are working on the scene. some queues in the area still.

the emergency services are on their way to stre aker vei, just after the exit from the e6. traffic accident, a car is on its roof. the extent of the damage is unknown, but probably serious.stre aker vei is blocked in its entirety from exit e6.
material damage only. the vehicle involved is now being towed away. traffic is flowing again now.
the emergency services are moving to the area of the nationaltheateret tram station. report of car against tram, extent of damage unknown.
