we are in meierisvingen following a report of a car against a person. the incident happened at low speed, the person is being cared for by health.
the persons will be reported for the relationship, and the remaining fireworks will be confiscated.

the police are in the vinderen area after reports of loud bangs, screams and shouts. turns out to be someone who set off fireworks. has control over two suspected people who are in possession of fireworks.
the fire brigade will remain on the scene for a follow-up inspection. we leave the place and a case is opened.

e6 ryenkrysset. we received several calls about wagon trains that wobbled and that had been in the ditch while driving. thanks to observant fellow road users, we were able to stop the wagon train. driver is drunk - he blew to far above the legal limit. he is taken in for sampling.

we have driven the stretch without seeing anything of the person in the roadway. there are many indications that those involved have got over the road and are now on safer ground. we generally do not advise anyone to cross a high-speed road as a "shortcut" to the other side.
we receive several messages about a person who is going to walk in the roadway on the e18 under the bridge at mcdonalds asker. we are on our way
the pipe fire is extinguished. there are still high temperatures in the pipe, so the fire brigade is carrying out subsequent extinguishing.
the fire service confirms a pipe fire. the smoke in the area has subsided.
the fire brigade is on the scene. no residents shall be exposed to smoke.
at bstadryggen. we and the fire service are on our way to deal with a pipe fire with heavy smoke.
the stalled car has been removed. traffic is moving as normal.
e18 exit at asker. car stopped immediately after the collision from asker in the direction of drammen. the car stop comes on a little too soon for other road users. we are on our way.
the cars removed. the road is open and traffic is moving as normal.
the stretch e18 below the exit to kongshavn is now closed for a short period due to recovery of the cars
e18 exit mosseveien under the exit to kongshavn. two cars have been involved in a minor traffic accident. they stand somewhat awkwardly in the roadway, which leads to slow-moving traffic passing by.

the likely sequence of events is a breach of the duty to yield. the driver of one car has his driving license temporarily confiscated. the same driver was taken to the emergency room for further follow-up of his health. case is created.
incoming v/ljabru. the police are on a traffic accident between two cars. this blocks the public transport field. no personal injury reported.

the woman has been found safe and has been reunited with her family. many thanks to everyone who contributed to the search, and a special thanks to you in the voluntary resources () who go out at all hours of the day.

two new cases of drunk driving in the last few hours.the first was stopped in greenland and did not have a valid driving licence. he was also drunk.the other was stopped at kern for driving at in the zone. we suspect that he was also under the influence of drugs. both are reported.

we are looking for a woman (65) with dementia who was last seen leaving the day center at frogner at around .she is wearing a knee-length dark gray uberjacket with a hood and boots. she is about cm tall and has almost white hair.

earlier this week, we also received reports of attempted theft/fraud using the same book purchase mode.if you or someone close to you has experienced the same thing in recent days, contact the police.

a woman (90) was called by someone who wanted to buy books from her. shortly afterwards, two pleasant men in their s appeared at the door.they tricked her so that she was robbed of a gold chain before they left the place. we are investigating the matter.

the moped rider has been taken to the emergency department with what appears to be a broken leg. we suspect that he was driving an unregistered "moped" with electric propulsion that should have been registered. we are therefore establishing two criminal cases.

we are in the greenland camp after reports of a traffic accident involving a moped and a car. the moped driver is examined by the ambulance at the scene. the person is conscious, but probably has broken bones.

we have had a laser check in the zone in bleikerveien at bleiker vgs. drivers received fines and points.one driver was measured at km/h. this gave him new dots in addition to the he had before. this means confiscation of the driver's license for months.

we have control over a car driver who is drunk in centre. the suspect also does not have a valid driver's license. the car he was driving also has minor collision damage, the circumstances of which are being investigated.
the car in question must have left the scene before the emergency services arrived. traffic is moving as normal
e134 just before the entrance to the elgskausen tunnel in the direction of the oslofjord tunnel: single accident - no information on serious injuries. this leads to queuing. we are on our way
everything is now in order at the scene and the emergency services are leaving.
the emergency services are on their way to the greenland camp, where propane is said to have leaked. the leak has been stopped. the fire service carries out the necessary measurements.
the car has then been removed and traffic has returned to normal.
a detour is recommended via lrenveien, petter mllers vei and further down haslevangen.
kernveien car with a stop which creates a number of traffic challenges. we are on site until the car is recovered.
the fire is extinguished.
fire in a car in heimdalsgata. we and the fire brigade are on the scene.
we are at grnerlkka after a report that several people were fighting. we have control over several people and are working to find out what happened.

a patrol has had traffic control at the bus terminal in oslo. nine motorists received simplified notices for mobile phone use. one driver's license confiscation due to too many dots. one is reported for running a red light.
bilberger has towed the wagon train to a nearby bus shelter. both lanes are now open to traffic.
bilberger is on the scene. working with the car that has problems. patrols on site direct traffic past the train that is having problems.
a truck with a trailer has had technical problems on the e16 near brenna, up towards sollihgda. both lanes are blocked. we have sent a patrol, and tow trucks are on their way.

we have been twice to an address on teisen to reduce noise. the second time we came in, we were threatened with a hammer by the person in question. after repeated attempts at dialogue, the person concerned was taken under control with the use of an electric shock weapon.
a case is opened for damage, driving under the influence and the passenger is reported for handing over a motor vehicle to a person under the influence.

after questioning the parties at the scene, we are left with the fact that damage has been done to a door in a hallway. in addition, two people are brought in for further investigations as we suspect one or both of them of having driven a car while intoxicated.

we are at grnerlkka following a report that someone had a fight at an address. we have control over those involved and question the parties to clarify what has happened. a person has a small injury in a hand.

the search for at least one perpetrator is still ongoing. both tactical and technical investigations are being carried out at the crime scene. it currently appears to be a targeted incident, and there is no information to suggest that there will be a danger to other people in the area.
we are in nydalen following a report that shots have been fired inside a restaurant. there are no people injured. the search for at least one perpetrator is ongoing.
the car has been recovered, and all lanes have been opened to normal traffic. queuing delays must be expected.
due to vehicle stoppage on the e18 exiting bellevuedumpa, there will be quite a queue. tow truck works on site. traffic passes slowly in one lane.
the vehicles have been removed from e6 and they write a damage report. only talk about minor material damage.
between the skullerud dump and the mortensrud exit, in the right lane in the direction out of oslo, two trucks have been inside each other. this creates traffic challenges on site.

the police have taken control of two burglars in operagata. they have broken open several stalls and taken various objects from them. they were caught red-handed and have acknowledged the relationship. they are arrested and taken into custody.
it turns out that this is a pure case of illness and therefore no police case. health follows up.
the emergency services are in mllergata after receiving a report of a fall accident at the site. first aid is applied to one person.

the driver of the car was checked out by an ambulance on the spot, only talk about a few scrapes. bks has taken both the moose and the car with it and vts is clearing the last remnants of the roadway before it opens fully shortly.
the right field is blocked until the elk is removed.

motorist who has hit a moose on stre aker vei southbound at the haugenstua exit, the moose is still in the road. the police and the game board are on their way. probably no personal injury. motorists are asked to exercise caution.
one of our dog patrols has arrested a person who has gained access to an unoccupied building. the person concerned is reported for burglary and possible damage.

we have stopped a car that was driving the e18 towards oslo without lights and initially refused to stop for the police. it turned out that the passenger was wanted and the driver of the car was suspected of driving under the influence. a person is taken into custody and the driver is taken in for an extended test.
mesta/vts has improved the ice swelling in the tunnel. all three fields are now open.

crews from mesta have closed off the water leak. now it remains to remove the ice swelling that has occurred in the right field. it is not known when this will happen, but work is being done to solve the problem.

reporter reacted to the driving behavior of another motorist because he wobbled and almost collided. we had the car stopped at tveita. the driver has blown over the legal value and will therefore be reported for drink-driving.
in the eastbound, a line connected to the extinguishing water has cracked and it is spraying out into the roadway.vts only keeps the left field open until the damage is repaired.
the cars have now been moved to the public transport lane, which is blocked. traffic flows slowly past in two lanes.

the police are on the scene of the accident. two cars involved in a rear-end collision accident. there should be no personal injury, but some material damage which means that there is a need for tow trucks for both cars. traffic passes slowly in one lane. this creates a queue.

the emergency services are on their way to the e18 at hvik, direction towards oslo, where two cars have collided. we do not know the extent of the damage. the cars are in the middle field. the traffic passes calmly by the place.
the moose managed to get off e18 before our arrival.

at the height of hagalkka on the e18, there is a moose moving back and forth in the lanes. we have a patrol with an animal shelter on the way who will try to get the moose out of the way. other motorists are asked to drive with care in the area.
the fire is now out. no personal injuries.
the emergency department is moving to a building adjacent to ikea furuset. report of a small fire at the site. everyone must be evacuated.
no fire, only a relatively poor attempt to cook something.
the emergency services are on their way to an address after a report of smoke coming from downstairs. not sure if there is a fire, or some other reason for the smoke.
the fire is now out. there has been some smoke in the area, but this will clear on its own shortly. burned out car is towed away. no people injured.

the emergency services are in konghellegata, where a car is on fire. no risk of spreading, and no one was injured. the fire probably started while driving. there is no indication that the car was set on fire.
a small fire in a kitchen is now under control. no risk of spreading. the fire brigade ventilates and has good control. no one is likely to be exposed to smoke.
the emergency services are on their way to an address after a report of a fire. uncertain extent. information may indicate that everyone has been evacuated from the address.

an observant motorist reported to us about a fellow road user who wobbled while driving on the e18 exit at asker.we stopped the car at liertoppen. the driver was drunk and did not have a valid driver's license. he is reported.

people have inhaled smoke and received extra attention from amb. none of them need further health supervision. some apartments are uninhabitable and residents are looked after by health. other evacuees are back in their own apartments. the police have secured clues and are investigating the fire.

there has been a fire in an apartment on the second floor, the fire has now been extinguished. this has created heavy smoke production. the riser that caught fire has now been evacuated and all residents have been accounted for at the assembly point. amb is now examining all evacuees, and as of now no injuries have been reported.

the emergency services are now on the scene and confirm heavy smoke. some evacuees from the block are looked after by police and health in a neighboring block. obre is on its way in with smoke divers. some residents await evacuation and stay inside the apartment until contacted by obre.

the emergency services are on their way to tante ulrikke's road where heavy smoke has been reported in an apartment block. we do not know the extent beyond the fact that there will be smoke in an apartment and in the hallway.
we talk to witnesses and open a case on the relationship. the cause of the fire is subject to further investigation.
the fire must be extinguished.
the fire brigade is on the scene and is extinguishing the fire.
the emergency services are on their way to jerikoveien where an excavator is on fire. unsure if there is a risk of spreading.
we have taken control of a person who was walking with a knife in his hand. there has not been any kind of threat situation ahead. the person is taken into custody.
during the first hour of the day, we stopped different drivers at three different places in oslo, who all appeared to be under the influence. all three are under arrest for an extended trial.
a person broke several windows in an office building. melder followed and helped us keep observation until we got control of him at skyen station.
the tunnel has been opened and traffic is running as normal

the road is immediately cleared. the suspect has driven down the ramp from brsen and crashed into a car that was already in the tunnel. the suspect appears to be drunk and we therefore take the driver's licence. he is taken in for an extended trial.
a car has been stopped e6 outbound at teisen. it stands in the middle lane - leading to queues and slow-moving traffic. we are on our way to the location

the opera tunnel right after the collision from brsen, direction west, traffic accident. unknown extent, but there are several vehicles in the right lane. the emergency services are on their way.

lanes have now been opened up, and traffic is starting to flow a little better. but still some queue on e18.
traffic accident e18 outbound after collision from asker. traffic passes in two lanes. one person is being treated by the ambulance, who appears slightly injured.

traffic passes in one of two lanes past the site. there is a lot of traffic from asker and southwards on the e18. we have a tow truck on the way, feel free to let it out.

at the rykenveien x lvhaugen intersection, two cars have collided, it only appears that there is material damage. one car has to be salvaged and this causes a number of traffic challenges on site.

the emergency services are working on a traffic accident at the end of the tunnel run to the svartdalstunnel at konowsgate. a car has driven into the tunnel wall. driver has pain in the upper body. svartdal tunnel blocked from ryen, as well as the entrance from konowsgate.

the police have stopped a car following reports from other road users about erratic driving and running red lights in the center of oslo. the car was stopped on the e6 at furuset. the driver tested positive for narcotic substances and he is taken in for further tests. case is created.

the same patrols had a check on bjlsen this morning.2 drivers received a fine of nok and points for mobile phone use.two were stripped of their driving license because they ended up with and points respectively after mobile phone use now.one was reported for mobile phone use because she did not accept a simplified order.
the emergency services are almost ready on site. the police collect information on the spot and from relevant parties and will open a case, primarily to clarify the causal relationship.

the development of smoke has subsided and it is confirmed that it originates from the brakes on the train set. there is no danger of this developing further. the evacuees from the train set and the platform of track are taken care of on the spot.

the emergency services are on their way to oslo s where there is smoke from a train standing by the platform. we are in contact with the train conductor and the initial information is that the smoke originates from the brakes on a train set. no personal injury reported and evacuation has started.

we have had a thorough traffic control on mosseveien. drivers were fined for driving illegally in the public transport zone, and one driver was reported for the same after he did not want to accept the simplified proposal he was offered.

we can move the three vehicles involved out of the roadway. one of the drivers has minor neck injuries and will be examined by the ambulance.the lorry has rammed into the car in front, which in turn has rammed into the car in front of it again. all vehicles are drivable.

there has been a collision between a truck and a car on the exit from trondheimsveien down towards sinsenkrysset in the southbound direction. we are on our way to the location to speak with the parties. no personal injury reported.
unclear if anything has been removed.
there is a broken window. the owner of the company has been notified.

should be at skoglund on the e16. the police are now unloading cars, as he was prevented due to queues.

exit from e6, going towards trosterud. truck standing across and blocking the entire field. the police are on the scene.

tow truck is on site. police and fire crews direct other traffic until the road can be fully opened.

spikkestadveien between ryken and spikkestad. traffic accident between two cars. material damage, but probably no personal injury. the emergency services are on the scene.work is being done to open one lane for other traffic.
the pedestrian was taken to hospital for a check-up. not seriously injured. we open a case.
mandalls gate. person hit by a car. undetermined course of events and extent of damage. currently being treated by paramedics on site.
the road is opened.
major problems with traffic management up towards sollihgda. a truck train with a stop blocks the roadway.

a vehicle has spun and hit the median ramp at the intersection of e-134 and slemmestadveien. there is only material damage to the vehicle, no personal injury. it is very slippery on the spot, which one can go a long way in assuming is the cause of the accident.

the fire has been extinguished, and all residents can return to their respective apartments.

frydenlundgata. we are on our way following reports of a fire in a block of flats. several who have evacuated themselves. must be talk of a smoldering fire in the sofa. as of now, no information on personal injury.

tsentunnelen westbound. truck stopped in the right lane. tow truck is on its way.
it turns out that the one driver is not trapped as first thought. the driver cannot get out of the car, as the car is placed close to the guardrail. appears ok.
naturally creates traffic challenges.
a person should be pinned down, but is conscious.
ring eastbound at kern. report of a traffic accident between two motorists. the extent of the damage is currently unknown.
there has been a fire in a boiler room at a company. the fire brigade has control on the scene. two employees are taken to the emergency department for a check-up after inhaling a lot of smoke.
we are done on the spot, a case is opened on the relationship. the tramways must ensure a larger hole in the fence.

looks like the car skidded off the road, through the fence that separates the subway track from the road. the car is some distance away from the live network and is now being towed back onto the road. no personal injuries.

midway between gaustad and ris subway station, a car has driven into the subway track. the emergency services are on their way. the subway is stopped past the place. the car must stand with its front half down in the track.
we finish on site, security of the area is taken care of by the building owner. we are creating an investigation into the relationship.
we and the fire service are in gteborggata after several bricks have fallen from a block of flats onto the pavement.
in parallel with technical and tactical investigations at the crime scene, the search for the perpetrator(s) is still ongoing.

two injured people have been located and are receiving the necessary health care. they can be described as not life-threateningly injured. as of now, there is nothing to indicate that there is a danger to other people in the area.
we are in the area of the national theater and vika following a report that a person has been shot. work is currently underway with first aid on site. the search for the perpetrator(s) is ongoing.
we have finished on site, the fire brigade will remain on site. there is major damage inside. we are filing a case on the relationship.

there will be heavy smoke coming from the nd floor. no one should be inside the building. the fire service is working to locate the cause of this.

car with a stop on the e18 right after asker in the direction of drammen. patrol is on the scene. a tow truck is on its way.

the car has extensive material damage, and because of this the paramedics want to take the driver to hospital for further examination. driving under the influence of alcohol is suspected. necessary securing of evidence is carried out. in addition, the driver does not have a valid driver's license and will be reported for this.
we are at the intersection of gamle ringeriksvei and griniveien following a report of a traffic accident. only one car was involved, and the people involved appear to be unharmed.

the emergency services are in ullern all after smoke has been reported from an apartment. the fire brigade is inside and working to locate the cause of the smoke. the apartment has been evacuated and no one appears to be injured.

our patrol reports cars with major material damage, no injuries to people. bilberger is on site and begins cleaning.

police are on the scene. box truck involved. people in the car. no one is stuck.

is a traffic stop on the e18 inbound at ulvya. don't know the reason, but we will be on the scene immediately. no reports of traffic accidents so far.

it was a taxi in which the passenger had been a bit violent and ended up partly on top of the guardrail. the passenger has been taken to the emergency department for further follow-up. the driver was not injured in the incident. e6 is opened.

we remind you about the test of the civil defense's warning system today at :00.siren/public warning system test today at noon.

person punched in the face by two people he passed randomly on the street. cuts to the lip and injuries to the back of the head.

not a serious injury, but one man is bleeding a little from the lip. based on witness information, it appears that one man provoked the other two ahead of the fight. this man has been in contact with the police twice earlier today, in relation to disturbances. he is arrested.
the police have just taken control of people in relation to a fight in storgata. we are investigating whether anyone has been injured and the causal relationship.
the suspect at bjerke is reported for driving without a valid driver's license. we no longer suspect drunk driving.

two new traffic conditions: we stopped an audi in greenland, affixed with a plate belonging to a bmw. the driver did not have a valid driver's license.at bjerke, a driver was too hard on the gas and was stopped by us. he also did not have a driver's license. we are investigating whether he is under the influence of drugs.
we checked a driver who appeared to be under the influence of drugs. saliva test at the site also indicated the same. we have therefore secured the necessary samples and are creating a report.

in the last hour we have stopped two drivers who did not have a valid driver's license.one driver stopped at bryn showed a fake driver's license, but the other driver stopped at ryen had no driver's license at all. both reviewed.
we have had a traffic control at the nordenga bridge. controlled drivers. a taxi driver suspected of drink driving and we follow up with relevant tests and a report.
the tow truck has then collected the car and the road is now clear again.

there is a traffic stop on e6 southbound, skulleruddumpa. traffic flows past in one lane and the area is well marked with yellow flashing lights. bilberger is now on the scene, and it will probably be a short time until the road is clear again.
the accident happened inside the parking garage.

all emergency services are at fornebu center after a car drove into and almost through a house wall. the car has extensive damage. one person is injured. we are investigating the cause of the accident.
the police have carried out investigations at the scene. no damage to the tunnel. the police are opening a case.
we are on our way to the vlereng tunnel, southbound run. the lorry has been stopped in the right lane after being too high and driving onto the roof.
the ekeberg tunnel is open to normal traffic.
based on the course of events, the driver has his driving license temporarily confiscated. case is created. the tunnel is still closed.
ekebergtunnelen northbound is temporarily closed. a trailer has hit the tunnel wall. probably no personal injury, but some fallout on the road.
we have control over a person who we suspect is the perpetrator. the person is taken into custody. case is created.
we are in brugata following a report of a person who has been stabbed with a sharp object. victims are taken care of by health.
strbil has been on the scene. the road is open to normal traffic.

in connection with a car driving into the ditch, the police have blocked off the road from the intersection emma hjortsvei/hyrabben and the intersection emma hjortsvei/tokes vei. this is because of mirror-gloss ice that is difficult to see. stroller is on its way.

a driver has driven into the ditch at hauketo. no injuries, but the car must be towed away from the scene. based on witness information, we open a case on the matter and seize the driver's licence. there is no suspicion of drug addiction.

we have several patrols in the sterkrysset area following reports that a young boy had dropped a firearm on the ground and taken it with him. we now have control of the boy and a softgun. we are now investigating this incident in more detail.
the missing are safe and sound. thanks to the voluntary organizations that were on their way to contribute to the search.

we are looking for a missing man with dementia who disappeared from ullern after .description: years old, fair skin, little hair / bald, approx. cm.possibly wearing a dark hoodie and dark trousers. should probably bring a dark/black bag. presumably a slightly unsteady gait.
the girl has arrived safely.
description: girl, half asian. approx. cm, dark long hair in a ponytail. black jacket with brown details, white shoes. uses glasses.
the police are looking for a missing -year-old girl. disappeared from thon hotell opera at about . tip to .
eastbound runs are now open.
the wagon train has now been driven out of the tunnel. the tunnel in the eastbound direction will be reopened shortly.
mechanical problem on the wagon train. will probably stay for a while. eastbound run is completely closed.
vehicle shutdown. the fortress tunnel eastbound. wagon train, car transport with stops. standing in the right field.
the patrol is finished on the spot. brought some fireworks. no reaction from the police.
report that fireworks are being set off in harsveien where some are also hitting buildings. must be in connection with a party in the area.
there have been incidents of fights between young people on the sea side of oslo s. we are on site with preventive patrols. we have control and no injuries have been reported.
the police receive multiple calls about slippery roads and difficult driving conditions in asker, brum and oslo municipality. if you do not need to drive today, we recommend that you leave the car
the police are now in contact with the boy. he is safe and sound.
description: boy, years old, small and thin, blond hair. wearing a blue jacket with dark blue arms. possible green hat. blue sweatpants with red stripes. speaking norwegian.
. missing boy. autistic. missing from brum hospital about minutes ago. the boy is not known in the area. tip to .
a car has driven into the wall of rema in stmarkveien. driver misses gas and brake. the driver's license has been seized.

a woman has been arrested for theft in dlenenga. the woman was checked on by a resident who surprised her. in a basement. the police now have control over the woman. unknown what she has tried to steal.

the police have control over the driver of a car that was stopped in operatunellen westbound. ran out of fuel. driver appears intoxicated. effects on drugs. the driver is taken in for an extended blood test. the car has been removed.
obre is working to extinguish smoldering in the construction. crews will be on site throughout the night. the police are opening a case and will carry out further investigations of the crime scene.
obre has the fire under control, but it has not yet been extinguished.
extinguishing is still in progress at the site. the smoke is harmless, but if it seeps into apartments despite closed windows, people are encouraged to leave the apartment.
there is a lot of smoke in the area and the police are reminding us of the importance of closing windows.

we are in enebakkveien where a fire was reported in a warehouse. there is a lot of smoke in the area and we ask that people who live in the area close their windows so that you are not exposed to smoke. no injuries or need for evacuation reported.
several wagon trains have been stuck in persveien from the roundabout at haralrudveien. the queue has been from esso at alnabru. persveien is now open to free traffic again.
the trailer has now moved on, the road has been opened.
the car has now been removed.
car with a stop on the e exit at asker. standing in the right lane and creating dangerous traffic situations according to reports to the police.
rdssen. semi-trailer standing across the roadway after skidding. slide down towards rdsen and mothellinga.
tungberger is on site. it is a bit tricky to remove the lorry, but they are working diligently on site.
the slovenian lorry has been removed from the hagabakkene and there is currently free traffic on the e18 outbound. however, there is still a slow-moving queue on the stretch.

we got the two drivers removed to write the damage report somewhere other than on the e18. no injuries and the bellevue dump has been opened.but; a wagon train stands still in the crab field to hagabakken outbound. tungberger is on his way.
two cars have collided in bellevuedumpa outbound. they are in left field. in any case, traffic is moving past the site very slowly, but recovery is on its way.
e18 outbound past asker is open again. the driver of the car that had spun and was hit by the lorry has been taken away by the ambulance, he appeared to be awake and not seriously injured.
a van has ended up across the hill gamle drammensvei near fyka. it is not possible to pass in any direction on the site. tungberger is on his way.

salvage is on site and we are working to get one field opened as soon as possible. somewhat limited possibility of a detour via asker centre. a person who was driving a car has minor head injuries and is being examined by the ambulance. e18 outbound past asker is still blocked in both lanes
there has been a traffic accident on the e18 outbound on the bridge over the railway. a lorry is blocking both lanes so that it is currently not possible to drive past on the e18 outbound.
the lorry which was the source of the traffic problems on slemmestadveien and rykenveien has now been removed.
we have assisted in winding the heavy hauler up to the site. work is now underway to remove the wagon train so that traffic can hopefully return to normal flow.
the traffic flows smoothly up towards sollihgda and we have not found any trains that create further kinks. we finish in the area for this time.

we have passed a trailer that is working on putting on a chain. this does not create extra queues. we are looking for the other one that should have stopped, but so far the traffic is flowing well up towards sollihgda.

a truck train that cannot get up from the dump in slemmestadveien/rykenveien is working on putting on a chain. this causes extra traffic on these roads. one lane is open past the site and we are directing traffic.
we have received a report about two wagon trains stopping on their way up sollihgda. we are on our way to the site to check the impact this has on traffic.

the fire service reports that the fire is under control and they have searched the apartment in question without finding anything. a person is taken to hospital due to respiratory problems after exposure to smoke.
we have finished on site, the road is open to normal traffic. one person to the emergency room for a check-up. we create a case.

it is confirmed that there is a strong fire at the address. the fire brigade is in the process of extinguishing efforts. a lot of smoke in the area which settles low in the area. close windows and vents.
the emergency services are on their way to vlerenggata after reports of a fire in a building. smoke has been reported and several people have evacuated themselves.
the emergency services are in kongsveien, about meters before the old seamen's school. a traffic accident, appearing as a car involved. limited access past the site.
we have checked a vehicle. the driver is suspected of driving under the influence of drugs.
the vehicles have been recovered and gone from the scene.
slemmestadveien by rykenveien. two wagon trains with a stop. there are major problems with traffic management. it is possible to drive rykenveien in the direction of asker.
driver taken for extended test. driver's license seized.

e6, bridge over e6 at linderud. fewer traffic accidents. two cars involved. suspicion of intoxication on the part of the driver of one of the cars. the road has been cleared so that traffic flows normally. no personal injury.
car removed. traffic flows as normal.
e6 exit at skullerud. car with stop. puncture. standing in the right field. the traffic passes slowly. salvage is requested.

nho holds annual conference in oslo spektrum. during the ifbm conference, the police will be highly visible in central oslo, both with motorcades and securing various objects. this could lead to temporary stoppages in traffic, but we will make this as short as possible.
we are on site and have solved the problems. traffic flows well at the site now.

at the intersection of strmsveien x alnabruveien there are several trucks that have stopped. they struggle with the hill up towards terminalveien and have to put on a chain. other road users are advised to find all roads past the site if possible.
on the e6 inbound at mortensrud, we received several reports about a tire lying in the roadway. this will be removed quickly.
car with a stop on the e6 exit at lindeberg. vts has a patrol car on site. don't know the reason for the shutdown.
we have taken control of two people who have committed violence against another. the victim is hit with an object and receives health care. the two suspects have been taken into custody.
no fire on site. likely ignition in a fireplace and smoke generation due to this.
the emergency services are on their way to a report of a fire in a building.
no case from the police, we assist with recovery.
not a fire, one of the front wheels has exploded and there has been smoke due to this.
the road is open again in both directions.
the emergency services are on their way to a fire in a vehicle near solstadveien.
truck with trailer that has slid into another car. no injuries, but tanumveien is closed in both directions until recovery is in place.
the cars have been removed and all lanes are open again for normal traffic. the police are opening a case.
lrentunnelen. traffic accident between two cars, probably hit from behind at low speed. left field is blocked. traffic flows smoothly in two lanes.
the road has been reopened in both directions
the lane towards sandvika is now open again.
a truck has been stopped on the e16 between sollihgda and skuitunnelen. the road will be closed in both lanes for a period in connection with recovery of the lorry.
we are done on the spot. we are filing a case on the relationship. the carriageway is open to normal traffic.
call westbound at ullevl hospital. traffic accident between two cars. the emergency services are en route.
we constantly have to help wagon trains to pick up speed from inside the brynstunnelen up towards ryen. this means that we have to block ring to the south for traffic for short periods.
two wagon trains have stopped on the e6 outbound before and at the exit to lindeberg/trosterud. this also causes additional queues at the back.

we have now got a little better flow on ring up from bryn to ryen, so traffic flows a little better on the stretch.still slowly moving queue up from skulleruddumpa to mortensrud.we expect this situation to persist through the afternoon, so plan your driving accordingly.

to avoid unnecessary stops on the opposite slopes, lorries and road trains going south should use mosseveien rather than ring3/e6 via ryen and mortensrud.there is an almost stationary queue up from skulleruddumpa and this will continue beyond.

the snow has intensified and with that it has become difficult for several truck trains on the opposite slopes on the e6 up towards manglerud and up towards mortensrud from skullerud dumpa.we are working to get them off as smoothly as possible, but there is a slow-moving queue nearby.
the missing have been found safely in the immediate area.thanks to everyone who got involved in the search!

a patrol stopped a car with snow covered side windows. it turned out that the driver did not have a valid driver's license, and we suspect that he is also under the influence of drugs. we create various traffic cases.

the missing person was last seen on vestli tbane yesterday at . since then we have no information about where she has gone.we are still looking for her in the area with volunteer search teams and police patrols.see picture in the thread below.

the cars have then been removed and the e18 outbound has been opened to normal traffic. a person will be examined further at the emergency room with what appear to be minor injuries. we are filing a case on the relationship.

we are on site. one car is standing with the front facing the wrong way, and the driver of this car will be examined by an ambulance. until the car is recovered, there will be extra queues on the e18 outbound.
two cars have collided on the e18 exit at sandvika. the cars are in the left lane.no injuries reported, but the police are on their way to the scene with a tow truck.
the car has been removed by a tow truck.

a driver has driven into the guardrail on eastbound before the brynstunnel. salvage is underway. no personal injury reported.the car is so far out in the oncoming lane that there will not be much extra traffic.

a lot of snow has been reported for the next hours. we encourage everyone who is going out to drive in traffic to calculate plenty of time, drive according to the conditions, and ensure that they are well shod. consider whether to leave the car if the conditions get too bad.

we are looking for a missing lady who was last seen at around yesterday at her home in stovner. description: female, years, -170cm, afghan origin, hijab, probably black winter jacket to the knees and winter shoes. for observations or tips about observations, call .

the fire brigade has control of the fire. there has been a fire in the partition between the st and nd floors, where the housing unit on the st floor is uninhabitable. all residents are monitored. it turns out that two residents have inhaled smoke from the extinguishing work. they are supervised by the paramedics on site.
fire in semi-detached house. undetermined extent, but no one should be injured. the fire brigade is on the scene. police and ambulance are on their way.
we are finished on the spot, a case is opened.
a field is open past the site. we are still working on the crime scene investigation and questioning of those involved.
stre aker road inbound just before the entrance to the lren tunnel there has been a traffic accident involving a car. three people in the car, appear unharmed. the road is closed at the scene.

it appears that the passenger car has run against a red light and collided with the tram. the driver is a foreign citizen and is arrested due to the risk of evasion. we are in the final phase of the crime scene investigation.

we are on site, vkerveien is closed due to the accident. all people are out of the car and are being followed up by the ambulance on the spot. it does not appear that anyone has been seriously injured.
the emergency services are on their way to the furulund tram stop after a tram and a car have collided. unknown extent of damage.
the truck has been removed and the road is open.

we are in strmsveien by mcdonalds, a trailer has stopped at the roundabout. this means that the road is closed pending recovery. traffic chaos on site, those who can drive around other roads should do so.
the fire in the kitchen in the house has been extinguished by the fire brigade, and ventilation is being carried out. no residents are exposed to smoke.
the emergency services are on their way to a fire in a detached house. residents must have evacuated themselves. as of now the scope is unclear.
the car has been removed.
car stopped in the right lane in the lrentunnel, westbound. vts is on its way.
the bus has moved on.

e6 outbound just after the exit to lindeberg, an articulated bus is partially in the public transport field. we are on site and warn with blue lights. the reason for the stop is said to be that it is very slippery in the lane, and the bus did not get up the hill.
the car has been removed.
car stopped in the public transport lane on ring , eastbound, by storo. must have lost a wheel. bilberger is on his way.

a car driving on the e18 towards drammen from solbr drove into some lumps of ice that had rolled out into the oncoming lane after plowing on the motorway. the car sustained damage to the front and had to be towed away from the scene. no personal injury.

the missing were found by volunteer search crews in rough terrain not far from their homes. unfortunately, life was not to be saved. relatives have been notified.we thank all volunteers for their efforts in the search.
we have called out volunteer crews in the search for the missing. they will start in the area around the klokkarstua housing and treatment centre. the police helicopter is also in the area.

the police are looking for a missing man (55) who lives at . he was last seen at home in hestehoven yesterday afternoon/evening.the man has black long hair in a ponytail, about cm tall. probably wearing a black down jacket. he clearly limps when he walks.call if you have info!
a blood alcohol test was held this morning at frognerseteren. drivers were checked. none of them had a blood alcohol level. we are very happy about this.
bilberger has removed the car. the emergency services have finished on the scene and the road has been reopened. there was no personal injury. the police are opening a case into the accident.
when the police patrol returned to mcdonalds, the two exiles had left the scene. we have had a chat with the security guards on site and have finished at the site now.
the police open a case on the accident and follow up with the bus driver afterwards with an interview. emergency services ready on site.
is a car involved in this accident. some material damage, so tow truck requested. people from one car appear unharmed, but are checked by amb.
the emergency services are on their way to the e6 exit at karihaugen. there has been a traffic accident between two cars. we do not know the extent of the damage as of now.

people have been expelled from the site. there has been a scuffle between them, and one person has some minor injuries to the face, but does not need further medical attention. the latest development now is that two of the expelled are back and creating disturbances. the police therefore drive back.

a woman is hit by the mirror of a passing bus. she has been taken to okl for further follow-up. the bus had continued on, but we are in contact with the bus company to get in touch with the bus driver.
the police are at mcdonald's asker where there has been a tense atmosphere between some customers. ampert also against the guards on site. we unravel what has happened.
the emergency services are on their way to schweigaardsgate where a woman has been hit by a bus. not sure how serious this is.
still a lot of disturbances and fights in the center of oslo. we are now outside a number of nightclubs on such missions. mostly about minor injuries, although a trip to okl is necessary for some.

it is now calm in the area and we are reducing our presence. this is an area where we have registered a number of reports recently, including the use of unreasonable fireworks, but also disturbances. we will therefore work preventively in the area for a period in the future.

two people have been subjected to violence by the arrested person. they have minor injuries, but have been taken to okl for supervision of some facial injuries. the arrested person has been taken into custody and reported for the relationship.

no one was injured, but the subway station is closed. there is also furuset subway station because of youths who have set off fireworks inside and outside the station. the police strive to use some resources to prevent in the area in the future.
the police have finished on the scene. no one was injured and it is calm there now. this was a private party where a number of people came who were not invited, and who then created the disturbances.

the police have been inside a nightclub in hegdehaugsveien and taken a guest out. this guest has now been arrested as he was in possession of a weapon. there has been no threatening situation and those arrested are taken into custody and reported to the weapons act.

the police are in grensen, outside a pub on stortorget. there have been many disturbances there. among other things, a man (25) was expelled from the place, but immediately went back into the queue at the nightclub. was thus taken into custody, and reported for the relationship.

the police have been working in the haugerud area for a while now. there has been unreasonable use of fireworks when firing at people and buildings. fires have also been fired at the police and at vehicles, without anyone or anything being injured. we continue our efforts in the area.

the police are in gamle drammensvei where there was a report of about young people arguing and fighting at a private party. it is calm at the scene now and we have not come into contact with anyone injured, but are continuing to investigate.

the police are at smestad subway station where we have taken control of a man who has committed violence against another person on the subway. we are in contact with the injured person, who has a cut on his face.

the police are on their way to ellingsrud subway station where guards have reported fireworks that have been fired at them inside the station area. no injuries have been reported. the subway station is temporarily closed and the police will contact the guards on site.

constant reports of unreasonable use of fireworks in connection with metro stations. this means that we occasionally check tram cars to make contact with the culprits. we try to avoid unnecessary delays on the subway because of this.

another driver tried to evade us, but finally had to give up after a short run on lower sinsen. the suspect appears under the influence of drugs and does not have a valid driver's license either. we create cases and secure a blood test.

a driver tried to get away from us, but we were able to stop the car in a parking space in stlfjra. the driver moved to the passenger seat, but we didn't go five on.the suspect did not have a valid driver's license, so he is reported for this and for evading control.

it has been a manageable start to the new year's celebrations in the oslo police district.about % of our logged missions in the last few hours are about unreasonable use of fireworks. a teenager was also reported for this at the bottom of karl johan at p.m.
very happy new year! wishing everyone a good and safe celebration tonight.this applies in oslo:

.hanshaugen a patrol stopped a driver who the suspects did not have a valid driver's license. the suspicion was correct, and in addition the driver was under the influence of drugs. we secure the necessary tests and open a case.
there are three cars involved. no serious injuries.
there has been a traffic accident in the e18 westbound exit at lysaker. there are major traffic problems at the site.
the car has been recovered.
the car has been removed, we are finished on the spot.
there is a car on top of the roundabout at hvik train station. there are many indications that one of the causes is slippery roads.
e18 exiting at ramstadsletta, a car has spun and been in the guardrail. minor material damage and we are waiting for tow trucks. the traffic flows smoothly past.
the bus terminal. girl kicked and robbed of her headphones. the victim followed the robber at a distance. he is now arrested by a police patrol.

the police received a call from a man who repented of his sins and said that he had been threatening a driver at borgen. we have now held a meeting between the parties, and he has apologized. questioning of the suspect is added to the case. good luck with a clean slate into the new year.

the police have searched the area with police patrol and dog patrol. we have not come into contact with any men we can link to the incident. the driver has been taken care of and we have received an explanation from her. she is unharmed, but naturally affected by the incident. the police are opening a case.

the police are at borgen looking for a man dressed in black for years. he contacted a car driver and was threatening, including by getting into the car and demanding to be driven to a nearby address. he left the car after a short time. we are in contact with the driver.
we and the fire brigade have finished on the scene. the car has been removed. case is created. the road is again open to normal traffic.
the fire is extinguished. the cause of the fire is unknown, but according to the driver, it started to burn while driving.
fireworks are also aimed at patrols on ellingsrud. we have control over young people who are suspected of having been involved in the incident.
right after the vlerengtunnelen exit to etterstad, the emergency services on their way to a fire in a car. exit lanes are naturally closed.

private individuals can only set off fireworks on new year's eve between :00 and :00. at other times of the year, it is not allowed, unless you have received special permission. fireworks must not be set off in densely populated areas, near dry forest or other flammable environments.
we are constantly receiving messages about unreasonable use of fireworks. among other things, that it is aimed at cars or people.
no case for the police.
the emergency services are on their way to edvard grieg's alle where there has probably been smoke from a pipe. residents have evacuated themselves.

we have taken control of someone who earlier today committed theft from a kiosk, in this act he lost his mobile phone. he was now back to collect this phone, which the police had in their possession. the person was arrested and taken into custody.
the bus has been removed.
bus with a stop in the right lane just after the lren tunnel, on ring at kern, direction ryen. vts's patrol car and tow truck are on their way.

the bus has been towed away, and traffic is moving as normal. it has not been possible to question the bus driver yet, but we have secured video and witness interviews. a case will be opened on the relationship.

there were reportedly few passengers on the bus when the accident occurred. no one is physically injured. it should not be slippery at the scene of the accident, so it is currently unknown what the cause is.
a bus has driven into a glass facade after colliding with some trees at lysaker station. we are on site. no reports of injured persons. we currently do not know the cause of the accident.
the police have control over two people who have caused damage at the subway station at carl berner. tagging.

police and fire service are at an address in bekkestua. less fire access. there have been open flames, but they have been extinguished. probably paper that has ended up on top of an oven. no people are injured.
police are on the scene along with an ambulance. people who were in the car. being investigated now. car recovery is on its way. major damage to the car involved.
car driven off the road due to slippery roads. storsandveien . no injuries have been reported. police are on their way to the scene. the car must not be in the way.
the bus has been saved. it runs from the site of its own machine. there have also been crews on site and scattered.
bus has run off the road. standing across dikemarkveien. so far no reports of injured people. the emergency services are on the scene.
the police are opening a case on the matter. the driver's license has been seized.

we are working on the scene interviewing witnesses. the driver of the car goes to the emergency room for a check-up. the car is located at a depth of metres, and salvage will take place when this is considered appropriate.
in connection with the unloading of cars from a cargo ship, a vehicle with a driver ended up in the sea. the driver was rescued on land and appears to be in good condition.
the bus has been removed. traffic is moving as normal.
ytre ringvei x tvetenveien, bus with stop. creates some traffic challenges. bileberger is on his way.
there has been no fire at the site. the powder device has been triggered inside an apartment. we have so far not succeeded in getting in touch with the occupants of the apartment.
it is likely that a powder device has been triggered. we are working to find out who may have triggered this.
the emergency services are on their way to ole vigs gate where there is supposed to be heavy smoke coming from a building.
the bus is waiting for recovery. vts takes over notification. the police leave the scene.
then one of the buses has started and has moved on. traffic is still moving slowly past the remaining bus.
we are on our way to dronning eufemias gate, where there are two buses blocking the traffic. unknown reason for the suspension of the two. this naturally entails traffic challenges.
we would like to thank everyone who was involved in the search for the missing, and especially the volunteer crews.
the person has been found.
the missing person has still not been found, call if he is observed.
the fire is extinguished.
the fire service reports that they have the fire under control. no information that anyone has been exposed to smoke.
advises the public to close windows.
this generates a lot of smoke in the area.
monrads gate. we are on our way to a report of a fire in a vehicle.

we are looking for a person who was last seen in the billingstad area. description: male, years old, norwegian, short haircut, gray shorts, black stilettos, grey/black hoodie with writing. in the event of an accident, call
we have arrested three people who we suspect were in the process of tagging in the subway area. thanks to observant security guards who reported to the police.
fireworks are not permitted except on new year's eve between pm and am, unless you have special permission.

. fireworks. the police receive many reports of fireworks being set off. several whistleblowers report tilde's unreasonable launching which may cause danger to others. the messages mainly concern younger people or young adults.

at shell mortensrud and the crossing dalssen there is a very smooth road surface. this causes vehicles, both large and small, to get stuck on the smooth road. as of now, the exit from the e6 towards mortensrud is closed until littering has been completed.
the cars have been removed. the road is open to normal traffic. no personal injuries.
e18 outbound after exit fornebu: traffic accident between two vehicles. undetermined extent of damage. there will be some queues.
the police have carried out a check of heavier vehicles that have arrived at hjortneskaia. a driving ban has been imposed due to a missing chain.
the car has now been removed. the driver of the car has had his driver's license confiscated, and is being reported for the matter.
the car is parked in the central concession, in kjlberggata. the light control at the kernveien intersection does not work. the municipality has been notified. traffic flows as normal.
ring (kernveien x finnmarksgata): traffic accident involving a car. lamp post/light control has been driven down. probably no injuries, but there could be traffic challenges.
the road is open again.
e6 exiting at ulvensplitten at the height of stre aker church. wagon train with a stop. creates traffic challenges, as it will take some time with car recovery.
e18 exit at lysaker. single accident. a motorist has had his car hit and spun. probably no injuries. but major material damage. the tow truck is on its way.
hammersborggata. a patrol was contacted by a person who had injuries consistent with stab wounds. the victim is conscious and is being cared for by health.
both cars have now been removed, and there is normal traffic on the e6 inbound at karihaugen.
the one accident only turns out to be a car that had a puncture. car towing is on site. the second accident is a single accident. major material damage to a car and the driver is slightly injured.

traffic accidents on the e6 inbound at karihaugen. we are on site. ambulance and fire service are on their way. in one of the accidents, a car has spun completely around but is now standing on its wheels again. currently unknown extent of damage to persons. the road is blocked in out of lanes. lots of queues.

we receive many reports of drunken minors in many parts of the district. there is everything from house parties with heavily intoxicated young people to young people who carry out vandalism along the street.

of those arrested, foreign citizens are in custody until at least sunday morning. the norwegians who were brought in have been released from custody.the suspects receive a punitive response, and that a legal assessment linked to the immigration act is carried out during the night.

then reports a car that wobbled and skidded in the middle of the entering . we stopped the car in and we now have serious suspicions that the driver is under the influence of drugs. he must therefore take a blood test. the car had not passed the eu inspection, so we take the plates too.
the emergency services are ready on the spot, we trace the cause to cooking.
we have investigated this case and found more information which means that we are not currently taking action on the reported relationship.
the emergency services are in contact with the resident, who reported a very thin layer of smoke in the kitchen. we are investigating the reason for this.
the emergency services are on their way to a detached house in stovner after a report of smoke.

we are at slettelkka following a report that a man in his late teens has been robbed of his jacket by three young men. melder was hit and kicked before the suspects fled the scene. we are searching the area with several patrols, as well as talking to the victim.

we have control of the car that was involved. we have clues and some information about who the driver may be, but we do not have control over him at this time. we are searching with several patrols in sandvika, including dog patrol.

we are in claude monet avenue following a report of a traffic accident. a child has been hit and the driver of the car has left the scene. we are searching for him in the area.the child is bruised, but does not appear seriously injured.

melder saw a person drive into the wall when he was going to park at a shop on . the driver seemed drunk, so the reporter called us.we have control over the suspect and he has blown far above the legal value on the breathalyzer. we have taken the driver's license and are opening a case.
we now have control over this situation in the city centre. people have been arrested in the case and taken to prison. we have no information about personal injury in relation to this campaign.

the police are now in the center of oslo with a lot of resources as a group of -40 people have wanted to express themselves. among other things, they have stood before the storting. this has not been reported and they have refused to comply with the police's orders. they will therefore be taken into custody.
the police have finished on the scene. the case will be investigated.

the emergency services have finished on the scene and the road has been reopened. one person is taken to okl for further follow-up. the taxi driver has his driver's license confiscated and the police open a case.

the driver appears unharmed, but the passenger was hit by the airbag and has tinnitus. amb checks the driver and passenger from the taxi. everyone on the bus is unharmed. information so far indicates that the accident occurred when the taxi was about to make a u-turn. we are still working with witness interviews and tracing.

the emergency services are on their way to drammensveien where there has been a traffic accident between a bus and a passenger car, a taxi. the message is that the taxi driver should be unharmed, but he cannot get out due to crushing damage to the door. there is material damage, so salvage has been ordered.
the emergency services are on their way to blsbortveien where a cyclist is said to have collided with a car. shouldn't be personal injury, but we are gathering more information.
the road is now open again. a claim report is filled in between the parties. one of the drivers is checked out at the emergency room after stomach pains.
we are working to move the cars, so that we can open the road again. the extent of the damage does not appear to be very serious.

the police are on the e18 exit at billingstad where there has been a traffic accident between vehicles. these are in the middle lane, while traffic passes slowly in lanes. amb is on his way to examine a person who has pain in the stomach region. some material damage.

the police are now carrying out a crime scene investigation at nordberg chapel where there has been a break-in during the night. this was discovered in the morning hours. there has been some damage done to the windows, but no information as of now if anything has been removed. the police are opening a case.
the police are opening a case.
the fire has been confirmed extinguished. obre will remain on site for some time to come.

the extinguishing work will take some time. sannergata will be closed at fagerheimgata until the extinguishing work is finished. the evacuees will be offered alternative accommodation until they can return to their respective apartments.
as of now, people have been evacuated from the block of flats. no personal injury reported on any of these.
in connection with extinguishing work, sannergate at fagerheimgata will be closed.
the emergency services are in sannergata where there is a fire in an apartment.
the person is arrested and a case is opened.
we have taken control of a person who was in possession of a gun, following a tip from security guards. there has not been any kind of threat situation..
traffic has started to flow again. one person was taken to hospital, but probably not seriously injured.

traffic accident e6 inbound at hybrten. traffic is at a standstill in all fields. tow truck is on its way. unknown sequence of events, but possibly a car that has spun. the driver is said to be injured, but the degree of severity is unclear.

a green van/lorry backing up with the tailgate down slammed into a parked toyota in tromsgata/snippen. the driver has examined the damage, but left without notifying the owner.we have been contacted by a distraught owner who is standing with a yaris front fender in his hand.
we have little to go on here. perpetrators are described as young boys aged -15, dark clothes, with buff over the mouth and nose. they ran in the direction of the ster junction.
we are in the nordseter school area. a report to the police states that a young boy has been robbed of his jacket. several younger perpetrators threatened with what are described as knives.
all vehicles involved have now been removed from the road.
fortunately, the incident was not as serious as first reported. one person has minor injuries in the form of scratches/cuts. received treatment by ambulance at the scene.

a bus and a car have been involved in a minor traffic accident on inbound at . the vehicles involved are at the bus stop.the emergency services are on the scene and one person apparently has minor injuries.
we are in pilestredet, following reports of a serious incident of violence. not sure what happened, but a number of police patrols at the scene.
e134 is now completely open again. less damage to both vehicles and people. the emergency services are ready at the scene.

the emergency services are on their way to a traffic accident at the roundabout down towards stre. no serious injuries were reported, but at least one car had to be towed from the scene. there is a lot of extra traffic on the e134 in both directions due to this accident.
the cars have been removed, and the road is open to normal traffic.
drivers are checked out by paramedics. probably not talking about serious injuries. tow truck is on its way.
ring at teisen, direction bryn: traffic accident involving two cars. undetermined extent of damage. brings traffic challenges and queues.

based on the information we have received at the site, the diesel spill may originate from a leak from a car that has been parked at the site. we open a case. the fire brigade takes care of the diesel spill in the water.

we and the fire service are at the boat harbor at slependen following a report that a good amount of diesel has leaked into the sea. about m x m field on the water which is covered by diesel spill. we are investigating the reason for this.
the train is still in place. passengers have now been evacuated from the train. there is still a complete stop to train traffic past the site in both directions.

driver of car checked by ambulance at the scene. appears undamaged. car has driven into the guard rail. a lot of damage to the car. not drivable. the driver has his license confiscated and we open a case. no queuing at the site now.
we and the fire brigade are there. only a little smoke and a fire alarm that has gone off. undramatic. no people injured.
all emergency services are in bogdstadveien after reports of a fire in an apartment. unknown scope as of now.
e18 exit at asker. traffic accident. a car involved. one person injured. we are on site.

we are on site. the person is seriously/critically injured and is now receiving life-saving first aid from the ambulance. there is a passenger train involved. we are now investigating the cause of the accident.
all emergency services are on their way to rosenholm train station after reports that a person has been hit by the train. the person must be seriously injured.

tyen/ greenland. we are in the area following a report of several young people allegedly throwing stones at each other. several young people are seen masked. no one is injured. in connection with the search for those involved, a revolver was found by our dog patrol.

there has been a collision from behind. no personal injury. car recovery is on its way. two lanes are closed and traffic is passing smoothly.
utg alnabru: traffic accident between two cars. they are in the right field. no report of personal injury. the traffic flows smoothly past. the police are on the scene.
the police came into contact with a party. a questioning was taken on the spot and a case of bodily harm was made. why the incident happened is still unclear.
we get a message that the fight has stopped. we are on our way to check what has happened. no injuries have been reported as of now.

no visible damage to the bridge other than scratches. it has been examined by competent personnel. subway traffic runs as normal.the truck was drivable, but had damage to the roof. we are filing a case on the relationship.

the police have stopped a car for a check on strmsveien. the police observed the car on the e6 and noticed some erratic driving. it turns out that the driver, a young man of , has never had a driving licence. he is thus reported for driving without a valid driving licence.

the road is cleared and we are done on site. only talk about material damage, we will open a case. regarding the sequence of events, it currently appears that the lorry has rammed into a stationary car.

e6 inbound between karihaugen and furuset: traffic accident involving several cars. queues and traffic challenges must be anticipated. the extent of the damage is currently unclear.

we are at storo following a report of a break-in at plantasjen. a person fled the scene on a scooter. we searched the area for a while and our dog patrol apprehended the man right near storo centre. the man was apprehended with the help of a police dog when he tried to flee.

the police are at the scene e134 near ryken in the direction of drammen after a car has run over a moose. there are no injuries, but the moose is unfortunately dead. the wildlife authority is on site. car recovery is on its way. traffic challenges on site.

work is still underway to clarify the cause of the smoke. as of now, no people who have inhaled smoke have been reported. around -150 people have been evacuated and will be guided into buses to keep warm.
to those residents who do not smoke in their apartment: you can remain in the apartment and do not have to evacuate.
the emergency services are in bjrnebrstien following a report of heavy smoke in an apartment building. working with evacuation. smoke divers from the fire service are in action.

we are aware that there is an ongoing conflict between several people in the area. we are now investigating whether this incident may be related to this one.

we now have more information about the incident. one person is still seriously injured, shot. no other people were found injured in the area. we are looking for a perpetrator who has fled the scene. we are not ruling out more suspects. the scene has been cordoned off and we are interviewing witnesses at the scene

we are still searching for one more person who may be injured. in addition, we are looking for one or more perpetrators. the person who was shot is seriously injured and is now being treated in hospital.
we are still searching for one more person who may be injured. we are looking for a man of action. we have cordoned off the area and have control over several witnesses.

we have several patrols at tyen center after one or two people have been injured in connection with a serious incident. there are many people at the site and it is very unclear at the moment. one person must have been shot, seriously injured.

the police want tips if you have seen or see the person in the picture (see next tweet). he is described as approx. cm tall, years old, somali origin, normal build, red t-shirt with a light jumper over it, black jacket, blue jeans and white shoes.

report of a fire in a vehicle in granstangen. risk of spreading to other cars. unknown cause as of now.

appears to be a single accident, where the accident victim has driven into a parked car on the spot. one person involved, who is attended to by paramedics on the scene. the person is conscious and awake.

the emergency services are ready at the scene. a person in the apartment in question has been checked out by ambulance after inhaling some smoke.the fire brigade has vented smoke from the hallway and apartment.
the emergency services have moved to a block of flats on lindeberg following a report of smoke. a small fire inside an apartment has been extinguished. so far no reports of personal injury.
the fire has been extinguished and the police are opening a case.
the emergency services are on their way to the car park outside the sporten pub after we have received a report that a car is on fire at the site. the car caught fire, but no one was injured.
the police have questioned the driver and are opening a case.

the emergency services are on the scene. the driver of the motorbike has been taken away by ambulance for further investigation. does not appear seriously damaged. the driver of the van has probably violated the duty to yield. drivers' licenses are confiscated.
the emergency services are on their way to tofteveien just after the exit to storengen, following a report of a traffic accident between a motorbike and a car. this must have happened close to maxbo.
the traffic on site passes slowly in the left lane. driver drops off car and hangs on site. it is estimated that several fields will open within min.

the emergency services are on their way to the e6 inbound at helsfyr, where we have received a report of a trailer that has hit a wall and some rocks have fallen into the roadway. no injuries reported, but will create a queue as there is fallout in all lanes.
we have now opened public transport in stortingsgata.the event has so far proceeded without any unwanted incidents.
the emergency services have finished on the scene, tow trucks have collected the car, and the road has been opened. the police are opening a case into the accident.

at the intersection of strmsveien/ole deviksvei, a car has crashed into a lamp post. the driver has pain in his back and has been driven okl with amb. there is extensive damage to the front of the car and the lamp post has hit a building which has caused some damage to the building. the traffic passes smoothly.

today at pm is the ceremonial opening of the th storting.this results in reduced accessibility in the center of oslo from now until around pm. this applies to both public transport and other traffic. follow directions in traffic, in the city center and online.
the car has now been removed and the road is clear again.

car has been stopped in the left field in the fortress tunnel. it stands before the exit to the center west. tow trucks and the police are on their way. vts has blocked the left lane with a light signal.
e18 outgoing is now opened as normal. there is a backlog from the morning rush hour and some queues must still be expected.

inbound traffic runs as normal in both runs on e18. outbound goes via bygdy all and over bygdylokket. follow the signs. the police have finished on the scene. the driver of the train is stable, no longer classified as critically injured.

then the wagon train is pulled up on its wheels again. it remains to be seen if it is runnable. the road must be cleared of fallout, oil spills and branches. traffic on the e18 inbound slowly passes the accident scene in the right lane. queuing is expected.
then we begin the work of straightening the wagon train. inbound runs on bygdy all from bygdylokket are blocked. outbound is open, as are inbound runs on e18.
traffic is going down bygdy all towards bygdylokket now. but it will be blocked again here when the recovery of the lorry is to be carried out.
then the right lane in the inbound lane of the e18 at the accident site is open to traffic. we will immediately open for traffic in bygdy all down towards bygdylokket.

the truck is on its side along with some downed trees. oil has leaked into the road. driver has been taken to hospital. e18 exiting at the scene of the accident will be closed for a long time. working to open at bygdylokket. currently closed there as well.

the driver of the truck is out. he is unconscious. there is smoke from the engine compartment, but no fire as of now. we are blocking all traffic, including over bygdylokket, until we have control over the heat generation.
e18 outbound/ southbound direction at bygdylokket: traffic accident where a lorry has overturned and is lying on its side. we are working on getting a driver out. both races are blocked.
the fire has been extinguished and there should be no smoke damage inside the school. is a living wall that has burned down. the cause is currently unknown. we open a case.
the police and fire service are at smestad school where there is a fire escape on the outside of the school building in a climbing wall or similar.

the cause of the accident appears to be a violation of the duty to yield in relation to field change. the driver's license of the driver of the car has been temporarily confiscated. the police are opening a case on the matter.
the vehicles involved have been removed, and the e18 has been opened up to normal traffic.

e18 ed. sandvika at the scene of the accident will be closed until further notice. follow the aforementioned detour. a tow truck is on its way, and we will endeavor to open the road as soon as possible. the people involved who were in the car are taken to the emergency department for further examinations.
all people involved are stable. the people in the car complain of pain. ambulance personnel are on site to attend to these.
the accident occurred on the e18 exit between the off-ramp to sandvika and the on-ramp from sandvika. motorists are asked to turn off at sandvika, and drive onto the on-ramp again.
e18 exit at sandvika: traffic accident involving a lorry and a car. the emergency services are on their way. unclear scope as of now. traffic challenges must be anticipated.
then the lady has arrived safely. she was found in the center of oslo by a police patrol.
