traffic accident between two cars, probably as a result of hydroplaning on one. one must have collided with the guardrail and the other must have driven into the ditch. no report of personal injury. we question the drivers.
it turned out that it was a matter of cooking/dry cooking which has resulted in a lot of smoke. the resident is examined by paramedics on the spot as the person in question has inhaled smoke.
report of a lot of smoke from an apartment in stre strandvei in tofte. all persons must be outside. possible cause is cooking.
a person on site who has inhaled some smoke, and is being checked out by paramedics. the cause of the smoke is probably cold heating, which has caused smoke in other apartments.
.hanshaugen report of smoke from an apartment in bjerregaards gate . the emergency services are on their way. unclear cause and extent.
it ended with a claim.

there was a lot of oil at the site which is probably the cause of the rollover. the driver of the motorcycle was taken to the emergency room. had back pain. the police are opening a case and someone will come to remove the oil.
police and ambulance are now on the scene. the cars have left the roadway. four cars involved. traffic flows smoothly. no reports of personal injury as of now.
all emergency services on the way to e18 inbound at strand. report of a traffic accident between cars. middle and left fields are blocked.
traffic accident. we and the other emergency services are in trondheimsveien after a motorbike has overturned. an oil spill on the road may be the cause. the driver is slightly injured.

there is extensive material damage to the cars. a driver is taken to the emergency room for a check-up. we also suspect that the driver of one car may have been under the influence of drugs. a case is opened and the driver's license is confiscated.

we and an ambulance are in nordveien following a report of a traffic accident. two cars have collided and one car has also driven into a fence. a total of people were involved but no serious injuries. we are investigating the cause of the accident.

we and an ambulance are on the scene. the cyclist is injured but not critically. getting treated by an ambulance now. no queuing on site. we are investigating the cause of the accident. the driver is at the scene and is being questioned now.
all emergency services on their way to a traffic accident in tvetenveien at tveita centre. motorist against cyclist. cyclist must be injured.

a car has driven into the guardrail and knocked over a lamp post at the grenseveien/ innspurten intersection. the car drove on towards bryn. we are searching for the driver and vts has been notified about the post.
the man who was missing in asker is safe and sound.
we are at vollen in asker after reports of a fire in a rubbish bin. the rubbish bin stood against a garage wall, which has suffered fire damage. the fire is extinguished.
the driver is checked out by paramedics on the spot. a tow truck takes care of the car. possible unwellness of the driver which may be the cause of the accident.
e18 outbound, in the tunnel at lysaker: single accident with a car involved. driver appears uninjured.
police patrol has control of a person who was in possession of a sword on the subway, at borgen subway station. no threat situation. reported for the relationship, and the sword has been confiscated.
the cars have been salvaged. queuing must still be expected.

car with a stop on ring at bryn. direction sinsen. stands in the left field. creates a lot of queues.
exit to lodalen is open to normal traffic.

we have come into contact with the driver of the wagon train. it turned out that the length of the wagon train made it difficult to make the turn. to avoid damage connected driver of the rear part. we salvage the trailer and will deliver it to its destination.

the driver fell asleep and drove into the motorbike, which in turn crashed into the car in front. a case is opened and the driver's license is seized.
traffic is now running as normal. the police are opening a case. one person was taken to the emergency room with minor injuries.
about arrested people have now been brought from the demonstration to the central detention center. the area by the embassy has been cleared and the police are in control of the site.
ring vestg. traffic accident between car and motorcycle. the police are on the scene. minor injuries. the traffic flows smoothly past.
two cars have material damage, tow truck on the way.
must have happened in connection with exit from sjursya.
e18 entrance at ulvya. traffic accident between a truck and a car. unclear extent of damage.

the police have re-established control of the embassy's property. we are still working on site to get a complete overview of the situation and other extent of damage. as of now, minor injuries have been identified to two people.

demonstration at the iranian embassy where many people behave violently and violently. several people are trying to get into the embassy. the police have a significant number of resources on the scene to restore control.
no report of personal injuries. case is created.
the emergency services are in storgata after a report of smoke. the fire service is inside the building and is working to get the fire under control. the cause is not known.
as of now, it appears that the person in question has carried out photography for tourist purposes. in today's climate and security policy situation, it is natural to investigate this thoroughly.
the person concerned is reported and arrested for the relationship.

we have control over a person who has flown a drone in the center of oslo. the person has flown within the no-fly zone that applies over central oslo. there have also been flights over military areas which are not permitted in accordance with current regulations.
the police are opening a case on the matter.
the person who was hit was on a bicycle. driven to hospital for health follow-up. denoted as not critically injured.

we have a suspected suspect under control. the case goes into the investigation track.

bjrvika tunnel westbound. car with stop. two lanes are closed, tow truck on the way.

the police have taken control of a man in trosterud after he threatened a conductor on the subway with a knife. we are questioning several people who were witnesses, as well as the conductor. none of these are injured. the arrested person has been taken into custody.

we have taken control of a man who smashed the window in one entrance to an apartment building. the man was arrested and will be charged.
we have taken control of an acting out man who committed damage. the man is arrested and reported for this.
we have taken control of a man who was very rude to the conductor on the train. the person concerned was tried to be expelled, but chose not to comply with the police's order. arrested and reported.
one person was taken to the emergency room with pain in the neck. probably been hit from behind. the driver's license was seized and a case is opened.
correction on the spot. we are standing on ring westbound approximately by teisen in the right lane. the traffic flows smoothly past.
eastbound: traffic accident between probably two cars. the police arrived at the scene now. no information on personal injury received as of now.

the injured person is a man in his s. injuries to the head and upper body.the police have control over other people who were in the apartment in question. these currently have witness status. further flow of information will clarify what status these get later in the case.

a suspected crime scene is located indoors and we have discovered weapons. as of now, we do not have information that indicates that we have to search for a perpetrator.witnesses are questioned. the scene has been cordoned off and will be examined by crime scene technicians.

the injured are seriously but probably not life-threatening. we are of the opinion that the incident does not pose a risk to others in the area. we are working with several hypotheses, including the possibility that the damage is self-inflicted. cont..
the police are in torshov with more resources. one person has probably been shot. we are in the early stages. we have control over the victim.
direction oslo: the police had control of cars driving illegally in public transport lanes. it ended with six simplified submissions.

despite a rainy night, drivers have been reported for drink driving in the last few hours.two drivers tested positive for alcohol in and respectively, while a young man appeared intoxicated while driving in centre.
we have held a traffic control in filipstadveien, cars checked, no reaction from the police.
the police are opening a case. the victim will be taken by ambulance for further investigations.

we are on our way to report a car and bicycle that have had a collision. apparently no injuries.

no traffic challenges. the police are opening a case.
collision between car and motorbike at the roundabout on mosseveien near srenga. motorcycle driver with a possible broken leg and is taken to the emergency room.

deer hit in vestmarkveien. no personal injury. the animal was so badly injured and suffered so much that the police patrol chose to euthanize the deer before the wildlife board arrived on the scene.
talk about dry cooking. no drama. the fire brigade vents out.

the police have held a blood alcohol test on the e18, entering at nesbru. checked about cars in just over an hour. driver with a low blood alcohol level.
the car has progressed.
car with a stop on the e18 heading west a little after the holmen exit. we are on site.

the driver of the moped is taken care of by health for further examinations and treatment. shoulder injuries. the driver of the car is reported and the driver's license is temporarily confiscated. case is created.
traffic accident between car and moped at esso in ullevl. happened at the roundabout behind the station. the moped driver is slightly injured. conscious, but possible dislocated shoulder.
there was a collision between a tram and a car in dronning eufemias gate. no personal injury. the parties fill in a claim report.
we conclude that china putters have been thrown and we are ending the campaign at bogerud.

we are in the bogerud area where several bangs or shots have been heard. so far, no one has come into contact with anyone who is injured or suspected. if anyone has seen or heard anything, we ask that the police be contacted on tel. .
traffic corps has held a check in vkerveien with a focus on drugs. out of checked, there were no reactions from the police.
the patient is freed and taken to the emergency department.
work accident at bryn. the emergency services are on the scene. a person has had his hand squeezed between two containers. the fire brigade is working on extrication. the patient is conscious.
e-18 inbound at nesbru, there is a traffic stop in the middle field, some traffic on the spot. police and tow truck are on their way.
the smell of smoke turned out to be from cooking. there is no fire at the site.

the fire service continues to work on extinguishing the scene. it is likely that a disposable barbecue caused the fire.
there is a fire in a rubbish shed in grnnegata. the fire brigade is in the process of putting it out.

it turns out that there are a total of nine cars involved. several of them are in need of salvage. there are also leaks from several of the cars. traffic is passing in a field for the time being. follow the mirrors so that the tow trucks arrive.
holmen e18 outgoing. chain collision. the emergency services are en route. five cars will be involved. undetermined extent of damage.
the police have held a traffic control at sandaker / north pole with a focus on cyclists. within minutes, cyclists were stopped and fined for cycling at a red light.
the fire service is still carrying out extinguishing operations at the site. the police are investigating what may have caused the fire.

just after at we received a report of several bangs from stmarka a little north of stmarksetra. credible reporter who believed it could have come from firearms. we have searched the area, but have not found anyone with dishonest intentions.
all boys are minors. they are reported for the theft and taken over by relatives.
then we have control over the "gardener's car". we also have control over boys who are linked to theft and driving the donning.
the car is green and is a -wheeler. it is battery powered and therefore we don't think it has made it this far.

missing persons have been found safe and sound. many thanks to everyone who got involved in the search.now driven back to institution.
we open a case on both conditions. it is not known whether it is the same perpetrator(s).

no personal injury. the roadway has been cleared and a damage report will be sent to the parties.
the emergency services on their way to mosseveien in connection with a report of a traffic accident. we are not there yet and the extent of the damage is unclear. major traffic challenges.
e6 inbound at ulvensplitten. car and truck involved. no personal injury or leakage reported.

we have had two incidents this afternoon where unauthorized persons have gained access to elderly people by offering massages. money has been taken from both addresses. one case was at lambertseter, while the other relationship happened at hvik.

the police are looking for a missing person with dementia. the missing person probably left the institution at this morning.besk: man, years old. nordic appearance. unknown clothing, but often wears yellow work gloves on his hands.tips or observations to

the car was recovered, and the road opened to normal traffic.
there is a vehicle stop in the eastbound direction of the lysaker tunnel. the left and middle lanes are closed while recovery is underway.
preliminary estimates from competent people on site are that the street can be reopened within a good hour. this estimate is given with the caveat that the situation may change.
the fire service believes the leak originates from rubina rana's street.tyenbekken down from greenland remains blocked until further notice.
there has been a water leak in the tyenbekken between grnland and schweigaards gate. the street is therefore closed until further notice. water & the sewage authority is on its way to improve this.
the stolen property has been returned to its rightful owner, the thief has been arrested, and the police are opening a case.

the dog patrol has just found the thief near the tennis courts. in his bag we also found the stolen goods he had stolen, including a couple of ipads.we are working in the area now to find out if he has been in several places.

just before midnight we received a report of a break-in at a home in lerkeveien in furuset. we search the area with a dog and other patrols.we have also received tips that the same person probably snooped on another door in the road shortly afterwards, so we have a good description of the suspect.
the girl has been found safe and sound. parents notified.

we are looking for a -year-old girl who has run away from her residence in sandvika. she is fair-skinned, wearing black shorts and a black t-shirt. we want information if you see someone who fits the description. both oslo and a&b are relevant locations.
kristian iv's street. we are on the scene following several reports of fights in the street. a car has fled the scene.
the police are in the process of terminating at the scene. no injured persons found. the police are opening an investigation into the matter.
the police are on the scene in the olafiagangen area in connection with a possible incident of violence. the patrols on the scene are working to get clarity on whether something has happened.
we received a message about a family of ducks that had taken the trip out on the e18 at ramstadsletta, we guided the family off the road, to an area with far less traffic.
the police are on the e18 exit at ramstadsletta in connection with ducks walking along the road. creates some queue. the patrol guides the ducks out of the way in a suitable place.
after a report of a deer that had strayed into a locked area at ekebergkaia, a patrol was sent with the animal shelter, which got the deer out safely.
one of our patrols has held a traffic control on the spot, out of checked, there were two drivers who were drunk. no reaction from the police.

one of our patrols has stopped a van where the driver had striking behaviour. if the control is blown, it leads to well above the legal value. the driver is reported and the driver's license is temporarily confiscated.

car stopped where the driver blows above the legal value on our breathalyzer. the driver has been taken into custody for further investigations. a case is opened and the driver has his driving license temporarily confiscated.
a patrol has seized two driver's licenses on e18 outbound. one measured km/h in the zone, while the other was measured at km/h in the zone.

the woman who was in the track has been taken to the emergency room, not seriously injured. no one else had been on the track.unrelated to this, guards had problems with a young man on the platform as well. he was taken to the emergency room and reported for damage to a police car and assault.

we have control over three people involved in the case. we are working to clarify what role these have. these have superficial injuries which are examined by the ambulance.

we are at oslo s after a report of someone running into the train tracks. one of these tried to hide under a train, but he has now come out. it is still unclear whether everyone who was in the trail is out. three people have been arrested on the platform by us so far.

we are with an ambulance at aker brygge after a report of an episode of violence at a night club. we have not received reports of anyone seriously injured, but we do not have a complete overview of what has happened yet.

a security company received a burglary alarm from a community center in kalbakken. at the scene, we were able to control a young person who had been inside. he explains that he had found some keys. we talk to him and testify on the spot.
melder had extinguished most of the fire before the fire brigade arrived. something has burned in a garbage shed. we are filing a case on the relationship.

minor damage to a motorcycle, no injuries to speak of.
the police are investigating a suspicious death in frogner. it is too early to say whether this has occurred after a criminal act, or whether it is a natural cause of death.
traffic accident crossing wergelandsveien - parkveien. uncertain extent of damage, but probably not serious damage. some traffic challenges.

in an apartment we now have control over a person who threw various objects, including stones and potted plants, down from the th floor of a building. a taxi has suffered damage to the windscreen, but we have not come into contact with any people who have been hit.
the police stopped a car where the driver blew above the legal blood alcohol level. the driver's license is confiscated, and the car is parked.

a boat from the red cross is in contact with the person in the water. he was in good shape, not injured. in any case, the person gets a check by health personnel.

car that has collided with another car in sofienberggata. leads race from the spot. we have taken control of him after a run. must be material damage to the car he collided with.

two cars and a scheduled bus are involved. three passengers who were on board the bus are being treated by the ambulance at the scene, extent of damage unknown, but they were conscious when we arrived.tvetenveien is closed in both directions until further notice.
we have received a report of a traffic accident involving a bus and at least one car on tvetenveien by subway. the emergency services will be on the scene soon.

the fire service reports that they have extinguished the fire, but that they will work on extinguishing it for many hours into the evening.the housing unit where the fire started is uninhabitable. we are still on the scene together with the fire brigade.
we have had a traffic control in nylandsveien. the focus was on turning bans out of dronning eufemias gate. in total, fines of nok each were issued for this.

the emergency services are in langgata after reports of a fire in a building. the fire service is working to put out the fire and the building is still burning.no injuries reported, but there is a lot of smoke in the area.

we are done on the spot. the driver of the car has been taken to the emergency room for a check-up. probably only talking about minor personal injury. the road has been reopened. we are opening criminal proceedings on the matter.

we are on site. there has been a collision between a bus and a car. no passengers on the bus. the driver of the car is being examined for health. probably no or minor personal injury. a complete standstill in traffic at jernkroken towards the city centre.
the emergency services are on their way to stre aker road inbound direction at jernkroken, report of a traffic accident. unknown sequence of events and extent of damage.

the swedish armed forces (heimevernet) have exercises in the areas of oslo, asker and brum. the civilian population must be notified of this. the norwegian defense force apologizes if this incident has caused unnecessary fear.

many residents in the area of kolss, rykkinn and skui have called the police's emergency number in connection with hearing many bangs, probably from firearms at around . we have been in contact with the norwegian armed forces, who confirm that they are the ones who fired practice ammunition.

another arrest has now been made in the case. the last person arrested is a man in his s. he was also arrested in oslo, but in a different place than the first arrest. we are continuing to work on the case and do not rule out further arrests. we are also seeking to clarify whether shots were fired.

the police have now arrested man, he is charged in the incident at prinsdal. the arrest was carried out without drama in oslo. we also have control over what we believe to be the dark car in question.

the emergency services and tow trucks are ready on site. the woman has been taken to the emergency room for further treatment, has injuries to her face. the police have seized the woman's driver's license and will investigate the accident further.
the emergency services are in sundbyveien/nrsnes where a car has driven out and ended up in the ditch. the female driver is breathing and awake, being examined at the scene.

the police have finished on the scene. the accident happened in the roundabout and the cyclist was hit so that she ended up on top of the bonnet of the car. she is being treated at the emergency room. the police are opening a case into the accident.

the police have carried out a number of investigations in the area, but still cannot conclude whether shots were fired. we have finished with searches and investigations and the case is now moving into an investigative phase.

the patient was taken to the emergency department for further treatment, pain in the back and head. the roundabout has been reopened and traffic is returning to normal. the police will open a case into the accident.

the driver of the scooter has been taken to hospital for further treatment. we do not have details about the extent of his injuries, but he was conscious and alert when he was taken to hospital. we have not come into contact with the driver of the car that drove away from the scene. the case is being investigated.

there has been a traffic accident in solliveien where a cyclist has been hit by a car, in a roundabout at lysaker. cyclist is monitored by paramedics on site, extent of damage unclear, but has pain in back and head. there is a slow flow of traffic up towards lysakerlokkett.

police and amb are on the scene. the driver of the scooter is supervised by amb. he is lying on the ground and is conscious. the car involved has driven from the scene in the direction of majorstua, we are searching for it.
the emergency services are on their way to kirkeveien, ring in the ullevl hospital area where there has been a traffic accident. a scooter and a car are involved. unknown extent of damage.

the police are still working on questioning the informant and searching the prinsdal area. we cannot confirm that shots have been fired, but we are working to clarify this. we have not come into contact with anyone injured or other witnesses to the incident.

the police are in the prinsdal area following a report that shots have been fired. we are in contact with the man who reported this, he is unharmed. we are searching the area for men and a dark car. it has been a short time since the incident and we are working on gathering information.
patient is followed up by health, appears as an accident. no action from the police. we are done on the spot.
ambulance and the police are on their way to a traffic accident on srbrten. a sick person who has driven off the road, extent of damage unknown.
the woman has recovered safely.

cyclist has cycled on pavement. motorist probably violated the duty to yield when the car was about to cross the footpath where the cyclist was. the driver's license has been seized, partly due to many dots in the driver's licence. the cyclist is not seriously injured. will be taken to the emergency room for a check-up.

traffic accident between car and cyclist at gamle drammensvei , reported injuries to the cyclist. ambulance and we are on the scene. the extent of the damage and the course of events have not been clarified.
the police have then finished their investigations at the scene. e18 will now be opened to normal traffic.
a technical and tactical investigation will continue at the site for some time to come. it is unclear when the e18 will be opened to normal traffic.

the police have blocked the e18 at bygdylokket, after a person threatened several motorists with a knife. the police had to fire one shot at the person in question. the person is not seriously injured.
stopped a car driver at cirkle k in asker for funny traffic behaviour. the driver appeared drunk and refused to blow into the breathalyzer. driven in for a blood test. case created.
rykenveien in heggedal: traffic accident involving a car and motorbike. the traffic normally flows past, and the people involved appear slightly injured. attended by paramedics on site.
the oslofjord tunnel has been reopened.
the oslofjordtunnel is closed after a fire in a train. long queues on site. must be expected to be closed for a long time to come.

the norwegian armed forces (home guard) will hold an exercise in the center of oslo until saturday /09/22 in the afternoon. uniformed personnel with weapons and military vehicles can be observed. the use of practice ammunition or other things that emit bangs must not occur.
the police have now spoken to both parties. there is talk of a conflict regarding a pc. the police also have control over the knife that was used.
the police are at hersleb school following reports that a person has been scratched with a knife. the person is not seriously injured, only a scratch. the police have control over the suspect.
the woman was found safe and sound.

missing woman, years old. description: blond hair, fair skin, cm tall, thin. pink jumper, pink trousers with a flap - possible with a pattern, white shoes, light jacket, white trolley case. was away from mortensrud yesterday at . current for the whole of oslo. call for observation.

we are at the intersection kampheimveien / hellerudveien following a report of a traffic accident. cars have collided. two possibly them are not drivable. no people are injured. some queue at the site.
we have confiscated the driver's license since we suspect a violation of the duty to yield. suspects and witnesses have been questioned and dismissed from the scene.
the fire brigade has extinguished the fire. we are investigating information that some young boys hastily left the scene before the report came in.

all lanes are opened every moment. the driver of the rear car is taken by the ambulance to hospital for a check-up. he does not appear seriously injured. it appears as if this car was unable to stop and drove into the car with the horse trailer in front.
we are at a kindergarten at smedstua school where there is a fire in a dollhouse or similar.

traffic only passes in the left lane until further notice. this causes a lot of extra queues at the back until the vehicles are removed. the tow truck is on its way.unknown extent of damage to people and animals, but an ambulance and a vet are on the scene.

we are on our way to a traffic accident on the inbound just after the collision from holmen. two or three cars are standing in the middle field, one of these is pulling a horse trailer with a horse in it. current sequence of events unknown.
the cyclist is taken to hospital by the ambulance. we are interviewing witnesses and the driver to get details about the course of events. we are still on site.

we are at a traffic accident involving a cyclist and a motorist at the maridalsveien x kaj munks vei roundabout.unknown extent of damage to the cyclist as of now. some extra traffic in the area while we work on site.

the injured person has been treated and interviewed in hospital. his injuries are not life-threatening. we have interviewed several witnesses in the case, as well as securing other clues at the scene. no one has yet been arrested in the case.

: the police are on the scene with more resources. one person has been shot and has injuries to a leg. we are in contact with the injured person and someone else in an apartment. we are working to find out what happened. the injured person is taken to hospital.
ed. asker. the police stopped the car after being measured at km/h in an zone. a case is opened and the driver's license seized.
the fire is extinguished. we open a case.
the fire service is putting out the fire and confirms that there is no danger of spreading.
fire and police are in borggata where there is going to be a fire in a container. the container is about meter from some cars.

we are in the helset area where there have been some young people who have scared other younger children, including by displaying an axe. we have control over both the ax and two young people. no one is physically injured.
then the oslo marathon is over for this time. congratulations to all participants for a job well done.
we came into contact with the runner outside the tunnel at srenga. he was guided to a more suitable route in the direction of ekeberg.

we are on our way to pick up a runner in the ekeberg tunnel's westbound run. he was on his way up the svartdal tunnel, but turned around when he reached the opposite hill. doesn't appear like a marathon runner who has run wrong.the right field is blocked until further notice. be aware of!

we remind you that the home guard has exercises in several places in police districts these days. the training means that soldiers will be visible in the cityscape in many places, including the center of .

today is finally the oslo marathon! many thousands of runners will run different distances throughout the day.this results in reduced accessibility in several places in the city centre, majorstua, skyen and frogner.see for trail and logistics info.
we had a short alcohol test on rykenveien this morning. the check was short because the second driver who was stopped had too high a blood alcohol level. case created.

: the police received a report via guards of a burglary in a bicycle shop. we were present with several police cars. a bicycle taken away. no suspect arrested. we are filing a case on the relationship.
all emergency services are ready on site. no injuries and the police are opening a case.
the fire is extinguished.
probably burns in a grill. the patio table and living wall have caught fire. some have evacuated themselves.
: all emergency services on site. reports smoke and possible flames on a balcony on site.

the police received a report of a car that wobbled on its way beyond rykenveien towards gullhella. a patrol stopped the car, and the driver's blood alcohol level was well above the legal limit. driver's license confiscated.
unfortunately, we are not getting any closer in the search for suspects. the victim is physically unharmed, but receives follow-up from the patrols at the scene. case is created.

we are in the gjerdrums vei area following a report of a personal robbery. victims were threatened to hand over their possessions. it was threatened with a possible stabbing weapon.currently, we have a very poor description of the perpetrators.
e6 inbound approx. before the klemetsrud exit, deer grazing on the side of the road. motorists are asked to exercise caution.
the road has now been cleared and traffic can once again flow freely upwards.

the police received a report of a person, with an angle grinder, when he tried to cut through bicycle locks. at the scene, the patrol encountered a person with clearly dishonest intentions. he was not allowed to bring bicycles, but was reported for the attempt, as well as carrying a knife.
no serious injuries. two accidents close to each other. major traffic challenges in the northbound direction. salvage is on its way, but will take some time.
the police are not at the scene yet, but information received by the police indicates that there are no serious injuries, but that there are vehicles involved. expect queues in the area.
the emergency services are on their way to a traffic accident between possibly vehicles. uncertain extent of damage.

the police are on their way to a report about a traffic accident between vehicles. probably head to head, but at very low speed. a report to the police states that the driver of one car appears drunk. probably no injuries.
the fire is now out. some paper has burned on the floor of a toilet. in total, around students evacuated themselves. no one is physically injured.
the emergency services respond to reports of a fire at a school. possibly some smoke in a classroom. uncertain extent. evacuation is in progress.
the svartdal tunnel in the direction of ryen is open to traffic.
the cyclist is looked after by the ambulance personnel. the police are opening a case on the matter.
toftes gate: traffic accident between motorist and cyclist. the cyclist is awake and conscious. otherwise, the extent of the damage is unclear. police and ambulance are on their way.
the cyclist is described as slightly injured, and is taken to the emergency room. it appears that the cause of the accident is a violation of the duty to give way on the part of the cyclist.
the svartdalstunnelen direction ryen will be closed for a while due to a leak from a vehicle. the cleanup is ongoing.
bernt ankers gate: traffic accident between motorist and cyclist. the cyclist must be aware of the unclear extent of the damage.
the cars have been removed and traffic flows as normal.
e18 outbound, on-ramp from bygdylokket: traffic accident between two cars that creates a queue, and slowness in the flow of traffic. material damage only.

oslo city centre: traffic control in storgata. in just over an hour, drivers were stopped for driving in violation of the sign "no motor vehicle..."six of these adopted simplified orders on the spot. the other four did not want this and are therefore reported.
the accident occurred when being hit from behind after braking. the road is open and there is normal traffic.
the emergency services are in the center of heggedal. a car has run into a lamp post. it does not appear as personal injury, only material damage. work to clear the road is underway.
the queue slowly moves past in the right lane. major material damage to the vehicles involved. no reports of serious injuries so far.
traffic accident between two cars in festningstunnelen eastbound. the accident happened in the left lane. traffic passes slowly in the right lane.

we have seized the driver's license of the suspected driver. the suspect tried to drive past the car in front as it was about to turn left. the suspect's car then ended up in the ditch, where it is now being recovered.

the police are on the scene and in contact with those involved. both cars involved must be recovered from the scene. sundbyveien is closed in both directions until the cars have been removed from the scene.the injured driver does not appear to be seriously injured, but is being treated by an ambulance at the scene.
the emergency services are on their way to a traffic accident in btst. two cars have collided and one has ended up off the road. sundbyveien at volloddveien is closed until further notice.

an electric scooter rider was reported for using an unregistered motor vehicle as the home-made scooter was too long in addition to other technical defects. an electric scooter can be a maximum of cm long.
we have had a traffic control at bjlsen. it ended with drivers being fined nok for using a mobile phone while driving.
the car and lorry have driven out of the tunnel on their own machine and both lanes are open to traffic.

we are at a traffic accident on trondheimsveien at the height of rommen where a motorist has driven into another from behind. the latter driver has been taken to hospital with neck pain.witnesses state that the suspect was using his mobile phone when this happened and we have therefore taken the driver's licence

traffic accident between a trailer and a car in the northbound bjrnegrd tunnel. the police are on the scene and in contact with the parties, no injuries reported. one lane northbound in the tunnel is open and traffic is currently flowing smoothly past the site.

the emergency services are ready at the scene. the resident who had inhaled smoke was taken to hospital by ambulance, but did not appear to be seriously injured.the cause of the fire is unknown, but the main theory is that it is connected to one or more electrical appliances.

we are in hybrtenveien following reports of a fire in a garage. the fire has been extinguished, but the fire service continues to work at the scene. someone who helped put out the fire has inhaled some smoke and is therefore being checked by the ambulance.
a pipe has burned. the police are opening a case on the matter.
the police have finished on the scene. case is created. as of now, it is unknown what has happened. no driver's license seizure.
the car has been removed.
possible lightning strike as the cause of the fire. no people involved. the fire service has control and we will open a case.
it is a bit unclear what happened and the reason for the fight. the police are opening a case on the matter.
control of the fire. theresesgate is opened to traffic again. no personal injury.
exit at aker hospital. car with stop. it creates traffic challenges. car recovery is on its way.
the fire service reports that they have it under control, but they continue to work.
it should burn well in an old cabin. it is reported from the fire service that the cabin will burn down. no notification that there are people inside. low risk of spread.
all emergency services on site. a possible fire in a pipe is reported. the fire service is working to locate where the smoke is coming from. theresesgate will be closed until further notice.
: report of a fire. a lot of smoke is coming from the rd floor. all emergency services on their way.
: message via the fire service that there is going to be a fire in a cabin. no notification that there are people inside. all emergency services on their way.
the cyclist is taken to the emergency department by ambulance. the police are making inquiries at the scene.
: report of a fight on a bus. we have control over six people. probably related to fights that took place earlier in the center of asker. we investigate further. no one injured.
: police and ambulance on their way to a traffic accident between a car and a cyclist.
we have control over three people. minor personal injury. we talk to the parties on the spot.
the police are on the scene after a fight between several people. we are working to find out what happened.
the restrictions on the site are lifted.
the fire is extinguished. the barriers must be maintained a little longer. we will open up as soon as possible.
the exit from e18 eastbound to the roundabout / bygdylokket is closed.
there are now open flames from the pump house. the fire brigade has started extinguishing efforts.
the emergency services are at the very heart of bygdy v/ bygdylokket. smoke development in a pump house.queen blanca's way in/out to bygdy is currently closed.

the cars have been salvaged. collisions from behind where the driver of the rear car is reported and has his driver's license confiscated.a passenger in the front car is taken care of by the health department for further examinations.case created.

one of two lanes is currently blocked at the site. heavy queuing.a person is examined by health on the spot, does not appear serious. a tow truck is on site and we will clear the road as quickly as possible.
e18 westbound after lysaker. traffic accident between two cars. the cars are in the left lane. the emergency services are on their way.
the fire started during welding work. no people are injured. the fire brigade will remain on the scene until the bottle has burnt out in a short time.the police set up an investigation case.

two people taken to the emergency room for further checks. no serious injuries suspected.the accident occurred due to braking, where the rear car was unable to stop.the driver's license of the driver of the rear car has been confiscated. case is created.
e18 before exit holmen, direction asker. traffic accident between three cars. a person complains of pain in the neckthe accident causes traffic challenges. tow truck is on its way.
the police have shot a hole in the bottle. it now burns out in a controlled manner on the outside of the building.
the police are now firing shots to puncture the bottle.

adjacent buildings have been evacuated. due to the development of heat in the bottle, it is now being considered whether the bottle should be cooled or punctured to avoid a further increase in pressure and the risk of explosion.
the fire is extinguished. the barriers in brobekkveien and haraldrudveien are reopened.
the emergency services are in place at brobekkveien where an acetylene bottle is supposed to be on fire. a safety distance of meters has been set.
we are done on the spot. the case is being investigated further.
the victim is being looked after by health, we are still working actively at the site with searches and gathering information.
police and ambulance are at tveita center where there is supposed to be a person injured by a sharp object. the person is awake and aware. perpetrator has run from the scene.
the missing boy has been found safe and sound.
clothing: navy blue jumper, possibly a hoodie on top. sweatpants. tip to .
the police are looking for a missing -year-old boy. pakistani origin. missing from address on hybrten.description; boy years, cm, black hair. only speaks portuguese and a little english.
the car has been recovered and the road is open.
car stopped at the roundabout. standing in the left lane. we are on our way.
the driver is examined further at the emergency room. no serious injuries.
single accident where the motorcycle has slipped and overturned. the driver is in some pain and is examined by an ambulance at the scene.the traffic challenges have been resolved.
ring between lren tunnel and sinsenkrysset, direction smestad. traffic accident. traffic challenges. the emergency services are on their way.

the emergency services are ready at the scene. only the motorcyclist who has been involved. the driver has overturned at low speed, appears to be slightly injured. being taken to the emergency room for health reasons. we are opening a case on the relationship

the emergency services are on the way. the driver of the motorcycle is awake and being treated by health care now. mosseveien is being cleared and will soon be open. there has been quite a queue as a result of the incident.
the emergency services are on their way to a traffic accident with a motorcycle on mosseveien crossing nordstrandveien. unknown extent of damage.
the semi-trailer has been removed, a case is being opened on the matter. the likely cause could be bad brakes on the trailer. the car is towed to the traffic station for examination.
the road is again open to normal traffic.
the accident is settled with a damage report. we will stay on site until the cars are removed by tow trucks.
we are on our way to another accident on the e18, this time the exit lane right after hitting sandvika. no injuries reported, but one car is not drivable.
the emergency services are on their way to the e18 inbound at asker. truck that has driven into the wall along the road. traffic flows smoothly past in one lane.

traffic accident between a motorist and a motorcycle rider with a passenger just below carl bernersplass, towards the city centre. mc is said to have been hit from behind by the car. no report of personal injury.
we have opened a case and seized the driver's licence. the kick cyclist was not seriously injured.
chain collision with three cars involved. hitting from behind. lots of traffic on the e6 inbound towards the accident site. bilberger is on his way.
report of a traffic accident on the e6 inbound at mortensrud. must be four cars involved. traffic slowly passes by, queuing.
report of a fight between several people at rdhusplassen. we are on site and have gained control of several people involved and are working to clarify the status and course of events.

the emergency services are on their way to kriveien at the krisletta roundabout where there has been a traffic accident involving a car and a girl on an electric scooter. there should be no serious damage.
the man is ready. thanks for the tips on the matter!

: the police are searching for a missing person. he is years old, white t-shirt, dark blue/black trousers, cm tall, kg, medium blond hair, blue eyes, a little beard. last seen at linderudveien. call the police on if you have seen him.
there will be a damage report. no personal injury.
police and ambulance on scene. the other car involved has driven from the scene. minor material damage to the car. we are investigating what happened.
: police and ambulance on their way to a traffic accident between two cars. a driver with a sore neck.
the stolen car has now been found again. it was parked in oslo at birkelunden. no one has been arrested so far, but we are now carrying out a crime scene investigation of the car.
the woman has recovered.

we are looking for a woman, years old, who has been missing from kern since friday september. about . she is about cm, long blond hair and blue eyes. probably wearing a slightly long beige coat and white trainers. call the police on tel. if you have information about the woman.
we are with several patrols in gamle ringeriksvei following a report of a fight between -6 people. a person is injured, being attended to by an ambulance. we are investigating the reason for this.

we are with several patrols in storgata after a fight between several people. when our first patrol arrived it had to request the assistance of several patrols to gain control. we had to threaten to use a baton to gain control.
no injuries have been reported, but a good deal of material damage has been reported. if the car is hit, call the police. we are searching for the car with several patrols.

we are in kbenhavngata after a report of a traffic accident. a car is said to have driven into other parked cars that were parked on the spot. the car then drove away from the scene. we are looking for a toyota prius, blue, with registration number br62333. the car has been reported stolen.

we are at grnlia by kongshavn after a report of a traffic accident between cars. one of the car drivers has run from the scene. we are searching with several patrols for this person. it is unknown if the person in question is injured.
car with a stop in brynstunnelen southbound. standing in the right field. we are on site and tow trucks will be in place soon. little traffic.

fire department now have control of the fire. it is still smoldering a bit, but they are in the post-extinguishing phase. the house has suffered extensive damage and is uninhabitable. the police will secure clues at the scene and open a case on the fire.
the road has been reopened. mopedist has injured his knee, but did not want further treatment at okl. the parties fill in a claim report.
the fire brigade is working to extinguish open flames and smoke from the second floor of the building. amb has examined the evacuees and reports that no one is injured.
bilberger is on site and takes the car with him. the road reopened.
on the e6 exiting at abilds there is a car with a vehicle stop. the police are on the scene and alert, while the tow truck is on its way to collect the car.

the emergency services are on their way to filtvet, rdstadhgda, where a fire has been reported in a house. there must be visible flames. the house must have two living units and no one must have been exposed to the fire, or inhaled smoke.
initial reports from the scene of the accident are that there are no injuries. amb will take a check of those involved. there is some slowness in traffic past the site.
the emergency services are on their way to a traffic accident in dronning eufemiasgate, at nylandsveien. a tram has had a collision with a moped. unknown extent of damage as of now.
traffic accident with material damage between two motorists in sinsenkrysset. traffic flows past as normal. no report of personal injuries.
the driver had tried to transport the boxes of furniture on a trailer, but did not secure them well enough. we open a case and the driver's license is confiscated.
there must have been an argument before one of the people involved took out a knife. the knife was taken from him and no one was physically injured. we have secured the knife and arrested the person.
we are at majorstuen subway station after reports of someone fighting. we have taken control of several people and are working to clarify what has happened. no reports of injured people so far.
in the public transport area on the e6 outbound, at alnabru, there are several large boxes of furniture that have probably fallen from a vehicle. police and vts are on their way..
the emergency services are ready at the scene. traffic restrictions have been lifted.
there has been smoke due to construction work on the outside of a commercial building. the situation is under control. no people are injured.

the emergency services are at stortorget following a report of a fire in a building. it does not appear dramatic and the fire service is taking the necessary measures.trams via mllergata will be prevented for a shorter period.

we have had a traffic control at eidssletta on rykenveien.a driver was reported for driving under the influence of drugs and that he did not have a driving licence.the nine other drivers checked were in order.
a patrol measured a driver at km/h in the zone on the e6 inbound at furuset. we have seized her driver's license and opened proceedings on the matter.
we have not come much closer in the search for the cause of the bang. we have secured video from the area and we are creating an investigation case.

we are investigating a report of a bang and several young men who ran from kontraskjret in the direction of the town hall at around :00.we do not know the cause of the bang, so we want to get in touch with witnesses who have information in the case.
the fire is extinguished. the cause of the fire is currently unknown.
the missing boy has been found safe and sound.
the fire brigade has control of the fire. small scope.
police and fire service are on the scene at vre rykkin after reports of a small forest fire.
if the boy is observed, contact the police on .
one of the cars involved is said to have made an overtaking which ended with it running off the road and ending up on the roof. the driver of this car has been taken to hospital for a check-up.

we are on our way to a traffic accident at stre where two cars are said to have collided and one is said to be on its roof. the persons involved must be out of the cars and receive medical supervision.

we held a traffic control at frogner park today. in three hours, motorists were checked. result: summonses for driving against a red light, for mobile phone use, fines for not wearing a seat belt, one reported for drink-driving and one for driving without a valid driving licence.
no persons in need of further health care. the vehicles have been recovered and the road is open. the police are opening a case.
a person complains of back pain and is taken care of by an ambulance. a tow truck is on site and we will prioritize getting the road opened as quickly as possible.
e6 entering skulleruddumpa. traffic accident between two cars. the cars are in the left lane. creates a queue. the emergency services are on their way.

we are in the holbergs plass area where there has been an attempted robbery in a -hour kiosk. the perpetrator has not received any profit. but presented a knife during the attempt. we are searching in the area.
a case is being opened and will be investigated further.

the victim was taken to hospital by ambulance. he was conscious and bleeding when police made contact with him. he is described as seriously injured.we are talking to several witnesses at the scene and are working to gather information about the sequence of events.

we are in vaterlandsparken following a report that a person has been stabbed.we are in contact with the man and he is immediately being treated by the ambulance. undetermined extent of damage beyond the fact that he is conscious.
melder was behind a wobbly driver who we have now stopped in grenseveien before carl berner. we suspect drink-driving and that means a breathalyzer test in custody for the driver.
the emergency services are in mrtelverksbakken after reports of severe dry boils in an apartment. there were no people in the smoke-filled apartment when the fire brigade entered.
rv , direction sinsen: closed due to stopped passenger car. detour via smestadkrysset.
the road has been cleared, and affected roads have been opened to normal traffic.
the northbound run of the bjrnegrd tunnel has been opened up in the left field. salvage is still ongoing. the exit to rud is therefore closed until further notice.

the driver of the trailer has been taken to the emergency department with smoke inhalation. the northbound run of the bjrnegrd tunnel will still be closed. clearing of the roadway and salvage of the trailer is ongoing.

the fire service has gained control of the fire, is carrying out subsequent extinguishing. the e16 and the bjrnegrd tunnel in the southbound direction have been opened up. northbound runs will remain closed until further notice.
the bjrnegrd tunnel is closed to traffic in both directions (northbound and southbound) due to a lot of smoke from the burning wagon train.
e16 exit at rud (after the bjrnegrd tunnel): fire in wagon train. emergency services on their way. traffic challenges and road closures must be anticipated.
the road is cleared. the ambulance has taken one person to the emergency room for a further check. the police are opening a case.

in connection with the accident, approximately liters of diesel leaked onto the road. the contractor is on his way to remove this.

e6 inbound at the height of starveien. single accident, car that has driven in the middle lane. the driver does not appear to be injured. major material damage. the probable cause of the accident is a puncture prior to the incident.

we are filing a case on the relationship. the taxi was not drivable and has been removed. we suspect that the taxi driver has broken the signage and he is therefore a suspect in this case. the tram runs as normal.

collision between tram and taxi in dronning eufemias gt x rostockgata. no serious injuries, but the taxi had to be removed from the scene with a tow truck. the tram cannot run west for the time being.

we are in contact with another person in an apartment on furuset who also has what appear to be knife injuries. he is taken to hospital.we are working to clarify whether these two cases have a connection, but preliminary investigations strengthen that theory.

the extent of the damage to the victim is serious. he is taken to hospital for treatment.we have investigated a subway that ran from the scene shortly after the incident. this has now been allowed to run from lindeberg further towards the city centre.we are at the furuset center with great resources.
we are at the furuset subway together with the ambulance after reports of a stabbing at the scene.the extent of the damage is currently unclear, but it appears serious.

the two arrested have been dismissed after they have been checked out of the case. we are searching the area with several patrols. if you have information (video etc.) in the case and have not given this to the police yet, we would appreciate it if you would contact us.

the subway is running as normal now.we have arrested two people in the area who we are investigating to see if they were involved. we have no indications that anyone has been injured, but this is not % clarified yet.
the matter has been resolved without the emergency services having to step in fully. normal operations at the site are being restored. we speak with employees on site.
the subway in the direction of the city center will be closed until we have clarified whether any of the people involved are on board.

we have received several reports of fighting or attempts to do so in connection with the tveita centre.initial information suggested that someone involved was carrying a knife. no information on injured persons.
there has been a fire in a garbage grinder at a company in alnabru. information received by the emergency services is that the fire has been extinguished, but work is being done to confirm this.
we have had the car removed and all lanes on ring are now open again.

a minor traffic accident on ring westbound before the tsentunnel. two cars involved and one of these has to be salvaged. the tow truck is on its way. until the cars are removed, there will be extra queues at the back.

a motorist drove past another car on storsandveien -5km after exiting the e134 towards filtvet. the car ended up in the guardrail and skidded off the road.no serious injuries. we have taken the driving license of this driver.

pedestrians are checked out by an ambulance on the spot. appears to be slightly damaged.

traffic accident between motorist and pedestrian. supposed to have happened at the intersection of fossumveien and aasta hansteens vei. the extent of the damage is currently unclear, but pedestrians must be aware.

report that two boats have collided at krkholmen. the passengers are ashore at krkholmen. no one should be injured. the police boat and patrols are on their way.

the police have finished on the scene. cyclist goes with ambulance to oslo emergency department. injuries still unclear, but not serious. the report is created by the police.
car that has stopped in the right lane, northbound in the vlerengtunnelen. the patrol car is on site. traffic flows as normal in other fields.

the police were called after two people argued and pushed each other at the kongen marina this afternoon. we have interviewed witnesses to the incident and the parties involved. there must have been an argument about the location of a boat.

driver's license bracket for the driver of the car. minor injuries. case is created.
also some material damage to the car. the accident probably occurred in connection with a violation of the obligation to yield.

report of traffic accident - car against pedestrian at smestad crossing. unknown extent of damage to pedestrians. the emergency services are en route.
the person concerned will be reported for unauthorized access and expelled from the premises.

current area may be somewhere in the direction of rvoll. missing people are very likely on foot, and will probably not use public transport or anything else. picture will come later.
the road is now cleared and open.
in the process of cleaning up the roadway now. the road will be opened soon.

not fire, but a person burning a fire. the fire service is investigating further, but there is no need for further agencies.
a person caught in the act by a security guard when he tried to break into an address. patrol is on the scene and investigating the situation.
no personal injuries. material damage, and provisional need for the towing of a passenger car. the accident occurred in connection with changing the file.

may look like it is a case of bodily harm, and not a robbery. some challenges in getting clarity on what has happened. patrollers are working to obtain explanations at the scene while we are also looking for the system man. no need for ambulance supervision.

the police have had traffic control on the nylandsbrua in the morning hours today. here, motorists were checked and no reactions. the control was aimed at driving under the influence.

hammersborggata/storgata. the police have three people under control following a report of a person with a knife who was in a fight with others. no one appears to be injured. it is unclear what is the background to the incident.

further details on the topic can be found here.note the difference in a mean. restricted area that informs about restrictions, and the area of nm from "military vessel" in which it is forbidden to fly drones and small aircraft.
granfoss tunnel, direction oslo, traffic accident between at least vehicles. it does not appear to be serious, but the tunnel will be closed in its entirety until we have an overview.

it is absolutely forbidden to fly a drone and fly within a radius of nm (about m) and height ft of the aircraft carrier.those who do so will be arrested, reported and the drone will be seized in connection with the investigation. the fine is around nok .

the police remind of the defined no-fly zone in connection with the fleet visit. this ban also applies to the use of drones.the police have taken control of several drone pilots. the reaction is the seizure of the drone and notification.

even today, there are many aircraft carrier enthusiasts out in the sun.this results in a slow-moving queue on mosseveien, as well as too many road users on malmya and ulvya.take local residents into account, as well as consider whether cycling or walking offers the same, or better, opportunities.
the emergency services are at romss, following reports of a fire. the fire is extinguished. the extent of the damage is currently unknown.

we have so far found vehicles with broken windows. we have been in contact with the car owners. there may be several cars with broken windows without us having caught it.the suspect in the case has been taken to custody.

mllergata. several people in a fight. no one else was injured at the scene when the police arrived. eyewitnesses say that the battle cocks have run in different directions from the scene.

we would like to clarify that the prohibition zone around the aircraft carrier is metres. the no-fly zone is similar, and up to an altitude of feet.
